animal.description:
Danny Boy is a handsome pure bred German 80 lbs. dog that is just 3 years old and a total sweetheart. He's come from a rough time his first 3 years of life, being chained to a tree with minimal human interaction. He is about 85% housebroken(likes to mark) and completely crate trained, although protective of his crate because it is his safe place. He is seriously lacking confidence in himself, but he is getting better by the day. Because of his old way of living, Danny is learning to be touched around the neck/collar area to attach a leash. He is uneasy and will grumble and growl to let you know it, but will not act on it. I've given him ample opportunities to see what he is capable of, but has never lunged at a hand. When he's free to roam, he is sweet as pie and will sit nicely when asked. He's good with kids, since he doesn't seem to see them as a threat, but I'd still say older kids would be best for him. He's simply learning to be a pet rather than a lawn ornament, so he has some kinks to work out. This boy must go to a fenced yard home and a GSD knowledgeable home. He is not to adopted as a guard dog. He will fail. Contact us at ccrtennessee@gmail.com

ADOPTION FEE REQUIRED. Contact ccrtennessee@gmail.com.

animal.description:
"Hi! Thank you for stopping by to read about me. I recently joined the adoptable doggy crew at Providence Animal Center's lifesaving facility from an overcrowded shelter in Florida. I am hoping you will stop by soon to meet me in person!  

My name is Shelley, and I'm around 2 years old and about 40 pounds. I'm all set to join my new family - already spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations.  

Don't tell the other doggos here, but I have quickly become a staff and volunteer favorite. They say that I am very sweet, gorgeous and just simply the best...aww shucks! They are still learning more about me, but the adoption center has scenic and serene grounds where you can walk me around and get to know me in person.

So, if you are interested in meeting me, please schedule an appointment here: ProvidenceAC.org/AdoptADog. My paws are crossed I will see you very soon! XOXO Shelley"

-------
During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!
-------

Providence Animal Center relies on adoption fees and donations to save pets! Adoption fees vary per pet. To find out this pet’s adoption fee or for more information, please call the Adoption Center with this pet’s ID number.

Can’t adopt? Consider fostering or donating! Visit https://providenceac.org/support-us/ for more information on how you can support the lifesaving mission!

animal.description:
All dogs are located in NY/NJ area

1y 25lb Nicole just got in from Puerto Rico!  She is the coloring of a Pinscher and the sweetness of the hound.  Not exactly sure what she is but sweet, on slightly shy side, and great w/ other pups.  So, who wants to help her learn about snow?  Please apply as these pups are getting scooped up quite quickly!  
.
Facebook: Zani's Furry Friends ZFF (weekly adoption event info posted there)
Twitter: zanisff 
Instagram: zanisfurryfriends
 
Dogs are spayed/neutered, UTD on age appropriate vaccines, Rabies vaxed, and microchipped (not Lyme vaxed but we seriously recommend it!)  All are in the NY/NJ area but we will adopt out of state to the purrfect home and in some cases, we can arrange transport.  Please go to our site zanisfurryfriends.org  and fill out an application 

Many of us (cats/dogs) will be on display on Saturdays or Sundays, weather dependent--please ask by writing us at info@zanisfurryfriends.org and following us on FB. If you are seriously interested in adopting one of us in particular, please fill out an application early Friday so that we can be sure to be there. Otherwise we decide based on other variables. Usually we are in our foster homes so this is a bit more stressful and a slightly artificial environment but we do want to be seen and find our furever homes too.
 
Please consider providing a home for more than one dog, especially if you are considering adopting a puppy. Dogs are pack animals and very much enjoy as well as need other dog company to learn to play, socialize and be good companion animals to people. The upside to this is that you won't feel as guilty leaving them alone and you get twice the love. Please come! And if you can't adopt, maybe you can foster or volunteer, and you can always donate!

 Louie is a 70lb male Boxer/Great Dane mix. Louie is a gentle but yet playful guy looking for his forever loving home. Louie loves going for walks and playing with other dogs.

Louie is crate and house trained and he has great house manners.

Louie will make a great companion for any family. 

Adoption donation fee is $250 which it is tax-deductible and goes towards the care of homeless pets with 4 Precious Paws Rescue. 

To expedite the adoption process you can download and fill out an application online at 4preciouspaws.org . All 4 Precious Paws Rescue animals are fully vetted:
*Spayed/Neutered
*Shots updated
*Micro-chipped
*Heart-worm checked and on prevention
*On Flea and Tick Prevention

animal.description:
We visited Mr. Bean over the week end and he is in need a quiet home to and enjoy his little life. He is very sweet and loves to be handled. You can see how hopeless he is in his eyes. He is 11LBS and is 7 years old. He was a stray and the shelter discovered he has a collapsed trachea. It is a congenital condition where there is a weakness in the tracheal rings limiting the amount of air that goes through. His exercise should be limited and we would recommend a harness always. Some clinical symptoms that can be seen with this condition are coughing/honking and fainting if too excited. Especially in the florida climate, daily walks should be extremely limited. It is highly recommended that animals with this condition are taken for routine annual wellness checks.
If you can help Mr. Bean and give him a great home please email us ASAP at pets@findahomegiveahome.com

Adele is roughly around 1-2 years old.She is a sweet girl who is very active, smart, and would love to go on walks or cuddle on the couch.Adele and her pups were found living under a bridge. We are currently working on house training and crate training. She is a playful girl who is looking for a family of her own and a home full of toys. 

Our adoption fee includes the spay/neuter, up to date vaccines, microchip, Interstate Health Certificate, and the transport service to get the new family pet to you. 

 Note: All dogs are located in foster homes in ALABAMA and will be transported NORTH AFTER ADOPTION. This means there is no way for a meet and greet before adoption. We try our best to give you honest personalities of the pup for you. We are more than happy to send videos, pictures, and even video chat so that you may have the connection with your pup before adoption. 

 All pets are delivered by a licensed transporter. 
The transportation company that we use is PETSLLC. They are well known and very professional. The link is listed, you are more than welcome to look and see what the closest drop off location is for you. 

http://www.petsllc.net/stops.php?route=9

 COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! If you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application!

 Please copy and paste the following URL for our adoption application:

 https://fs29.formsite.com/pickenscountypartnersforpets/form1/index.html

 Please be advised that our volunteers are busy rescuing, transporting, and caring for our animals. We will respond to your application as soon as possible. Upon review of your application, the rescue in Alabama will contact you, so you can ask any specific questions that you may have. 

 If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement.

 We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

animal.description:
Meet the infamous tiktok song litter! Chicken Wing, Chicken Wing, Hotdog & Bologna! Chicken & Macaroni, Chillin’ with my Homies! 

These 2 month old lab chihuahua mixes are ready to move on from their life of fame and settle into a forever home! These guys weigh between 3-8 lbs and will be small dogs when fully grown. They have typical puppy energy, enjoying wrestling matches with each other and chewing on bones, before settling in for a nap. Chillin & Homie are the smallest of the litter. They’re sweet pups who are ready for their forever family! Their adoption fee is $400.00.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

- Precious, preciousness!
- Survived a dog attack and then her “family” surrendering her to a shelter to be euthanized versus getting her the care she needed!
- Thankfully the shelter staff knew her injuries were fixable and this baby deserved a chance at life!
- We’ve repaired her jaw and her wounds are healing! Her spirit and loving heart have recovered and she is ready for a real family! - Needs a few more weeks of soft food and TLC! Full recovery expected!
- Typically happy, playful and silly puppy! 
- Apply here: https://wgsrescue.wufoo.com/forms/adoption-application/

IS IT LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT? 
To find out more about this adorable adoptable, please go to https://wgsrescue.wufoo.com/forms/adoption-application/ to fill out an adoption application. Once we receive your application, a volunteer will contact you. 

You can also find general information about our organization and adoption process on our website, www.snowcappedshepherdrescue.org (please note that the online adoption application on our website is not functioning properly - please use the link provided above). 

We do not have a shelter/facility - all of our dogs are cared for in private foster homes. We will review your application to determine if we have a good match and then set up a visit so you can meet your new best friend.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Are you looking for a super smart female that absolutely absorbs good training sessions and really loves working to please you? Then Coco is your girl!!!

Coco is a 8 month old Malinois x German Shepherd spayed female. She is just the sweetest thing, petite, moderate energy level. Like all young working dogs she needs to stay busy day to day in order to keep her mind working. This can be in the form of simple training around your house, having her as a running partner, or training her for bigger things. She already knows sit, down, shake (right and left). If you don't keep her busy you may find her trying to take a shoe or something else lying around (although she has not damaged anything while she's been with us). She loves her rope toys but to keep her busy and also to play with her brothers.

While she has a nice off-switch in the house, she is active and loves to play and hike and run. She is great on a leash. She's also house trained (has not had one accident during the few weeks she has been with us) and learned the dog door within the first 36 hours.

As with all young dogs she is still learning her way around other dogs. She gets along well with her two foster brothers one of which is happy to wrestle with her during zoomie time and the other has taught her that not all dogs love puppies picking on them and she handles that instruction from her foster brothers well. It's doubtful that she would be good with cats. She has a lot of interest in squirrels during our runs so her prey drive may be too much for cats.

Coco is crate trained and actually loves being in her wire crate. When she is ready for down time she wonders right into the crate and takes a nap. At bedtime she will head there as well (even when we try to spoil her and have her stay in the human bed).

Coco hasn't been around children but would probably be fine with dog savvy kids. She may not be the best if there are really young children. She is protective of her people but with proper introductions to both other dogs and people she seems to do just fine. If you are interested in making Coco a member of your family, please reach out to your adoption coordinator. If you do not have an adoption coordinator, please complete an adoption application at www.freedomgermanshepherdrescue.org.

animal.description:
Berry is initially the shy one but now begs for attention. Very interested in other dogs and loves being held. Although a bit smaller she can hold her own with her big brother.

Maya has a sad story; despite that she is very sweet and just wants affection. She was found on an abandoned property fending for her and her 8 puppies. We named them after shades of blue.

A Mother's Love

Mom scared and traveling 1-2 miles to a gas station for food to bring back to her puppies. So many wanted to catch her, but she had puppies somewhere and was not having it. 

Tracked to a horrible property, she warned her puppies and they scattered and hid. When food was left for her, she gently carried the bowls back to her puppies. She seemed to know the property, every in and out, every fence hole she navigated with ease. 

Slowly one to two at a time the puppies were found and brought to safety, but no chance of catching mom. 

Eventually when the rescuers thought they had all the puppies, they tried again for mom, but it wasn't happening. Why? Because there was still a puppy on the property. 

When the final puppy was captured, she followed the rescuers to their cars and with a little patience and time, she surrendered herself by bowing her head to the savior who had been feeding her for the past 9 months.

Do not fill out an application on this site- please read above to where to go for Snow White

PLEASE NOTE: This dog is courtesy posted for another individual or Rescue. Different policies and fees may apply.

MEET SNOW WHITE!!

It's me Snow White I'm approx 2 years old, and I'm a shy/timid girl who was never socialized around many humans. It takes me a bit to warm up, but once I do I love you!! I want to share with you my special day I had with a very nice volunteer.

She came to pick me up and take me out for the day to give me a break. She said I was easy to leash up, but once we got to her car I was scared, I pancaked to the ground, I really have never been in a car much, she ended up picking me up and placing me in her car, and once I was in there I was fine, she said I ride very nice in the car. I liked sitting in the middle watching out the window.

We made it to our first stop which was Papago Park, we met up with 2 other nice volunteers that brought dogs as well . I jumped out of the car I was a bit scared I didn't know what was going on, my friend said let's go on our walk and I started walking very nice on the leash, I don't pull, she says I'm so good on the leash. I enjoyed the smells all around. We passed by other people walking dogs, I never reacted to dogs or ducks. Sometimes people on the bikes would scare me when they rode up fast on their bikes behind us. I walked very well with the other dog buddies who came along, we met people. I walked up to them slowly, and sniffed them, and then I got lots of love from the humans, it was amazing!! we came across water I wasn't too sure about it, I put my paws in it and that's about it. After our 4.5 mile hike/walk we headed out to our next stop.

My friend took me to a nice place where I got a plain burger and ice cream cone. It was so yummy, check out my video. I never had one of those before. I had the best day ever! I really hope I have lots more with my new family!

Snow White needs a quite family, older kids 13 and over would be best for her. Someone who has some patience to help her know she is loved and be well taken care of and spoiled. She is a very sweet girl.

All dog adoptions include the following:

--Spay/neuter surgery

--Microchip

--Wellness exam through VCA Animal Hospitals

--Access to our Behavior Helpline for the lifetime of the pet

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Liara AKA Zola!

A 5-year-old, female Chihuahua mix with a sweet, mellow disposition. The racing stripe down my back is a non-itching variety of Alopecia most likely caused by a nervous condition. Some say it makes me look edgy. I get so nervous about things that my whole body trembles. But, with some TLC, I'll be your biggest protector and BFF.

Let's get this straight right from the start I'm a house dog and I don't walk on a leash! I enjoy backyard excursions and would love to keep you company out there. I'm working through some insecurity issues. New environments, car rides, socializing with people and other animals is all terrifying for me, but with a little practice every day, I think I might actually learn to like all of those things.

I'm kind of potty trained as long as you take me outside every few hours, but I expect you to read my mind. I can get inside using the doggy door, but haven't quite got the confidence, YET, to go outside on my own. I prefer to go outside together.

My favorite place to sleep is next to you. As long as I go potty before bed, I will sleep through the night. I would like to make friends with a cat, but they're super moody so I tend to keep my distance. I know some commands, but I don't follow them. How can I "come" and "sit," if I don't trust you, yet. With some patience, kindness, and understanding, eventually, I will do as you wish. Except for the leash thing - that freaks me out!

animal.description:
Bitsy, 7 years old, chihuahua mix, 9lbs

Bitsy came to us as a stray. She’s a friendly little girl who wants her person’s approval.  She likes attention but also seems to enjoy some alone time.  Her favorite place is the couch, maybe because it’s near the fireplace and toasty!

Initially she was very scared but she’s calmed down a lot once she adjusted to her new envrioment. (It’s probably pretty hard being a stray when you only weigh 9 lbs!) She is still frightened by loud noises and seems leery of men.

We believe she was someone’s pet at some point, since she is spayed and trained to use the pee pad. It only took her a week to get back to being fully house trained.

Bitsy is NOT a barker. She has an unusual little bark that you won’t hear very often. She is OK with other dogs, even if they’re large. She has been very interested in the outdoor cat; I think she’s happy to finally meet someone who’s more her size!

This sweet girl just needs some kindness so she knows she’s safe.  She’ll be a loving addition to someone’s home!

animal.description:
Sparky is a 13 week old Collie mix looking  for his forever home.  He is a puppy. So expect puppy shenanigans.  He is good with other dogs, and dog savvy cats.  Older kids as he is a puppy, so children who understand puppy antics!  If you are interested in learning more about Sparky, please complete an application and then reach out to Roxy@bigfluffydogs.com

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/. 

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
NOTE:
- May be ok with smaller dog in the home
- No children

NAME:
DOROTHY SHAW (named after a character from Gentlemen prefer Blondes)

AGE/GENDER: 1 year old female

BREED: Sapsali mix (Korean dog)

TEMPERAMENT: Sweet, affectionate, mild-mannered

WEIGHT: 25 lbs

HOUSE TRAINING: Good!

CRATE TRAINING: Good.

OTHER DOGS: Requires another dog (small) in the home. A dog who is outgoing and confident and can be a great mentor to Dorothy.

CATS: TBD

CHILDREN: No

ADOPTION DONATION: $475.00

HEALTH: Dorothy is spayed, microchipped, flea treated, dewormed, and is current on vaccines.

Your adoption donation goes toward offsetting the cost of this vet care as well as other incidental costs of care.

HISTORY: Dorothy and her sister was saved by our friends at Go Rescue Korea from a dog meat farm. They flew to the US to find a better life!

NOTES FROM FOSTER HOME: DOROTHY is a wonderful and sweet girl. She can be initially a little shy at first but loves people. One of her favorite things is jumping up for hugs. So many hugs!

She likes to cuddle and loves to sit by you and be in your company.

She is quiet and confident and independent but also likes friends and gets along well with fur friends.

SHE CAN JUMP! She is a great jumper so if the fence is easily scaled, she can climb up and get out. She's not one to trust to leave unattended in your yard, as these dogs can be escape artists.

All dogs adopted from Motley Zoo come with a leash and Martingale collar (or a harness, if necessary), depending on each dog's particular needs. Each dog also receives a "Tour Gear Bag" full of brochures, coupons, and supplies for your new pup!

ABOUT MOTLEY ZOO:

Welcome to Motley Zoo Animal Rescue! We are a rock and roll themed, volunteer-run, foster based, 501(c)(3) non-profit animal rescue organization based in Redmond, WA.

Motley Zoo is a FOSTER BASED organization, which means our rescue animals are cared for in private foster homes (or partnering pet stores) where the animals receive one-on-one care and attention in a home environment until permanent placement is found. We do not have animals available for casual viewing and same day adoption. Due to the volunteer run structure and decentralized/ virtual nature of a foster based group, an approved application is required to make an adoption appointment for any of our animals.

If you are interested in one of our Adoptable Roadies, please email adopt@motleyzoo.org and request an adoption application (the auto-responder also has a link to our application). We will work toward getting you approved as an adopter so that we can set a time for you to meet your new best friend!

Motley Zoo also runs "Rock Star Treatment Dog Daycare" in Redmond, WA where proceeds from this service, help support our rescue's vet budget- however, this is NOT a shelter. For more information about daycare or training, check out www.rockstartreatment.org.

Please visit our website www.motleyzoo.org for more information!

Thanks for considering adoption- we look forward to helping you find your best match in a furry friend.

Rock on-

The Motley Zoo Crew

ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/9944

Hi! My name is Remembering Coco and I'm guessed to be a Chocolate lab mix and guessed to be about 10 months old. I'm a sweet girl and I currently weigh around 63 lbs. 

Click here and here to see me in action!

- Housebroken
- Will go in her crate at night to sleep, but is fearful of her crate any other time. We have done some work on this, but right now she only stays and goes in her crate to sleep overnight. She destroyed a wire crate due to the separation anxiety and needs to relearn it's safe space at all times of day.
- Knows sit, down, shake, focus (eye contact), sit from a down, and we are currently training sit-stay, down-stay, place, and her recall. Coco has also done some training about loose leash walking but that is still a work in progress. She does wear a front clip harness on current walks.
- Good with other dogs especially off leash. She has some barrier frustration at not being able to get to or play with dogs on a leash.
- Best in a home without cats
- Loves stuffed and frozen Kongs as well as any digestible bones/ beef braids
To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description: Intake Date: 31 Dec 2020 ----- Age at Intake: Est 3 months ----- Breed: previous pups from this household tested as golden retriever shepherd and several other breed mix----- Size: 15 lbs ----- Status: Owner Surrender----- Compatible with: dogs, cats, children ----- Suitable for: home with fenced yard ----- Medical/Behavioral Needs: None known----- Additional Notes: Mando is quite outgoing! He is a handsome little guy who is into everything. Mando was born to a litter of 12, we were made aware they needed rescue and 5 came to us (unsure what happened to the other 7). They have not had a mother for some time from our understanding (around 4 weeks of age) so there is some vital socializing missing. We are working to get the mother fixed as this is her second litter and she is a tripod and really doesn't need to be bred repeatedly every year. Mando is a young puppy that came to rescue very small for his age. He will need a lot of socializing and exposure to make up for lost time. An adopter needs to ensure he is provided with a healthy environment to grow up in so that he is a well adjusted adult! -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- If interested in meeting and potentially adopting, please read the adoption requirements and complete the adoption application located at forbellessake.org. Once processed and approved a meet and greet can be scheduled and if a match an adoption can be finalized at that time. FBS standard adoption fee is $175. All residents are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, dewormed, microchipped, and treated for any known medical needs. Breeds are best guess. Housetraining is not guaranteed but crate training is worked on with all residents. A secure physically fenced yard is required.

animal.description:
Let's talk about the beautiful Dinah! What a gorgeous girl she is, friendly, playful, goofy and affectionate, she's ready to become your new best friend.

Dinah is a smart girl, who is very treat motivated and keen to impress her people. She knows her commands very well, Iike sit, down, paw, and will to go to her bed when told. She lives for affection and praise, and you can see her little mind working away to make you proud.

She's a playful girl, and although she enjoys playing with toys on her own she is so much happier having a friend to play with her. She has a good amount of energy and will happily play fetch for as long as you can keep up!

Dinah is house-trained and happy to spend time in her crate, but she does need some work on her leash skills. Or lack of skills! She does pull on the leash and can be a little excitable when she sees other dogs out and about. We think directing her focus on treats, combined with ongoing training, Dinah is smart enough to learn fast and improve her manners. She has interacted well with other large dogs. 

In the home she's very quiet, well behaved and snuggly. She will come over and put one paw up on you to request some extra love. She loves to lay around and relax with one eye open, watching you around the house. 

Overall Dinah is a very sweet, affectionate, well behaved girl who just needs a little training to make her an even better and happier, well rounded dog. This includes slow introductions to new environments, people, and animals - she can get overwhelmed if presented with too much stimulation all at once! Dinah will thrive in an adult-only home (no children under 16), with or without other large dogs, and *may* be able to integrate with a confident cat (although we aren't certain on this). 

Dinah is 1 year old, 50 lbs, and ready for her forever home! Please visit www.liveloveanimalrescue.org to fill out an adoption application.

est DOB:  7/28/16
current weight: ~ 25 lbs

We answer all emails back within 48 hours. Please watch your spam folders as an application will be attached and this sometimes places it in there. 

She is missing a hind leg, but it's not slowing her down. 

She is REQUIRED to be the only dog in the home due to resource guarding. She does fine outside of the home in dog parks and walks but in the home, it is hers. Training could fix this but we just require her to be alone with her humans. Also no small children that could reach for food or toys. 

Foster is ready to speak to the adopter and make sure it is 100% good fit. 

HIS/HER adoption fee is $550 USD and that will pay for TRANSPORT, all his/her shots up to date, neutered/spayed, microchip and rabies.

Please e-mail MuttsAndMeows@Mail.com for an adoption application. 

This dog is currently in the Houston Texas area.  Once the application is approved and adoption fee paid, transport will be arranged.

Because this adoption will be without meeting the dog first, we will need to try to be extra careful that everyone (including you) think this will be a good fit.  We will try to give you as much information about the dog as we can.  Unfortunately, many are fresh from the shelter and we don't know much about them yet. 

Like us on Facebook - search Mutts & Meows - and help even more pets find loving homes.

animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Chilo is a handsome 8-month-old Hound blend. He was found as a stray in a small town in Mexico where he faced a sad life of starvation and abuse. A Good Samaritan in that area stepped in to change his fate and contacted our rescue for assistance. Chilo was immediately transported to Texas and hospitalized because he had contracted both distemper and parvo. He beat the odds by surviving two deadly diseases. As a result of the distemper, Chilo does have a minor neurological twitch that does not impact his daily activity level. Chilo also did test positive for ehrlichia which is a bacteria infection caused by a tick bite and he is completing a 30-day course of doxycycline. Chilo is initially shy but once you offer him treats, he quickly displays his affectionate and loyal nature. He is an active and playful boy but will need leash training. His ideal owner would lead an active lifestyle and include Chilo in daily walks, hikes, etc.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
His adoption fee is $175. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, Tri-Heart Plus chewable tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

?

AGE: 8 years old

ENERGY LEVEL: Medium

MEDICAL HISTORY: Healthy, up to date on vaccines

IDEAL HOME: Experienced dog owners.  Secure fenced yard ideal.  

?

Lollie is an eight old Shih Tzu mix. She came to CHR in rough shape but has made a complete turnaround in 2 months. 
She is housetrained but needs a potty break every 4 hours during the day. She is also pee pad trained. Lollie loves to please her pet parents. She’s really a great little girl. Very loving and sweet. 

Lollie loves to play with other dogs but can start fights over guarding her foster mom. We think it’s better to play it safe and place her in a home without other dogs.  
Lollie has dry eye in her right eye, which requires daily drops.  Also, she has a cherry eye. She is scheduled to have surgery to fix the cherry eye in March.  

Lollie came to CHR with a really bad skin infection. She will still need a bath every week. 
Also, Lollie is on a special diet for her skin.  We are asking that her new owner to continue her on the high-end diet($90 a month) or a home-cooked diet, which cost much less. We can discuss all of this on a call once you apply to adopt her. 

Lastly, Lollie came to CHR very “mouthy” when being handled.  She has made amazing progress, but she still may be nervous once she is moved to a new home. CHR will provide training to you while she adjusts to her new home. 

Because of this, Lollie must go to an all adult home. Watch this video, and you will see how cute and sweet Lollie is.   https://youtu.be/s0d6CVbPaz0

Dog's Name: Francis
Estimated Breed : Beagle Mix
Approximate Age: 4-5 years
Approximate Weight: approx. 30 lbs
Currently Living at: Boarding
Adoption Fee: $300
DOG'S DESCRIPTION
Frances is a very sweet gal who loves people. She hopes to find a loving family to share some fun adventures! Will you cuddle up with this girl by the fireside in her new home?
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.
Please "like" our Facebook Page for the most current events and new dogs.
Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
~Good news for those of you looking for your one true love, Cupid's arrow struck early this year! Meet Ferris, a four month old southern gentleman. With a big doe eyes, super soft fur, and the most perfectly adorable ears! Perfect for your Valentine's Day snuggles, he's obsessed with kisses and hugs, and has the perfect wiggle butt dance moves for all your Valentine's Day dance parties. He's learning to have good boy manners, and sleep like a lamb overnight in his crate. Ferris is already a fan of the ladies, getting along with his two foster doggy sisters, one big and one small, and his three foster human sisters. he's already stolen the show and the hearts of everyone he's met since arriving in PA.

Please email us at AlmostHome4Dogs@yahoo.com to find out if Ferris is the right pup for you! (Local adoptions preferred - Philadelphia and tri-state area [South Jersey and northern Delaware] only.)

NOTE: Most puppies do best in the company of an older dog who can teach them "doggy manners," so homes with at least one other dog usually will be given preference in puppy adoptions. Please read Suzanne Clothier's wonderful article, "It Takes a Pack to Raise a Puppy!"

PLEASE READ BEFORE CONTACTING US! We are NOT a shelter: All of our dogs live in private homes with foster families. Come and meet the Almost Home dogs and their fosters at our Meet & Greet events, where you can learn more about our wonderful dogs from the people who live with them, find out which dogs are on their way and when they'll arrive, and fill out an application to adopt or foster.

We cannot adopt to homes where electric-shock fencing systems or training collars are used. For more information on the dangers of electric-shock collars, please visit banshockcollars.ca/studies.php and http://www.hollysden.com/say_no_to_shock.htm (scroll down and click on the "Invisible Fencing Systems" link).

We do not have an online adoption application; to request an application, e-mail us atAlmostHome4Dogs@yahoo.com. To speed e-mail processing time, be sure to note the name of the dog you are inquiring about in the Subject line. For Meet & Greet times and locations, visit our home page, where you also will find information on our adoption process and fees.

FOSTER FAMILIES ARE LIFESAVERS!! Can you open your heart and home for a few weeks to homeless shelter dog? Remember, by fostering a dog, you save TWO lives - that of your foster dog, and that of the dog who takes his place in the shelter! Come to a Meet & Greet and find out if fostering is for you - there's no reward quite like the feeling that you've saved a life ... or two!

Meet Jackson! Jackson is a 40lb terrier mix and approximately 2 years old. He is super sweet and his favorite thing to do is snuggle with his people. 

Jackson is great with the kids and dog in his foster home. He has loved on every guest that enters his house and greets them all with a wagging tail. He loves to play outside in the yard and run with his foster dog sister. He would stay out there for hours if allowed! He walks great on a leash and is always ready for a nice walk. 

Jackson is working super hard on his potty training and is almost there. He sleeps very soundly through the night in his crate and does well in his crate when his foster family is not home. His foster family likes to tell him that his heart is as big as his head. Kids or another dog would be a bonus in his forever home, so he has someone to play with. Jackson is very eager to please and would do great in any home.

We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family to approve an adoption. Please email adopt@safehavendogsIL.org for an application or additional details.

Please consider becoming a foster home while you search for your new best friend. We need foster homes - pounds are overflowing with puppies and adult dogs that are at-risk and need help. animal.description:
Girl look at that body, I-I-I work out! Hello, I'm Laila! I might look like a strong girl but I'm so gentle my foster family never need to worry about me. Here are a few things about me: 

-I'm COMPLETELY potty trained, I've never had an accident! 
-Oh my goodness, my foster mom thinks I deserve a PhD in walking on leashes! I never pull and always walk by your side. It's easier to handle me than my 13lb foster fur-brother! 
-I can be intimidated by stranger dogs, especially those bigger than me, but once I learn they are friendly I open up. 
-I have the perfect amount of playfulness in me. I'm not too energetic, but when my 13lb foster fur-brother wants to wrestle, I will entertain him. Despite being trippled his size, I know to be nice and gentle when I wrestle with him, and let him jump all over me. 
-My absolute favorite thing to do is sunbathing, but sometimes I can't decide whether I want to be inside with the humans or out under the sun, but I'll scratch the door to let you know. 
-Crates are not my favorite, but I settle down quickly. 

Overall, I'm a really smart, loving, and nice girl. My ideal family would be one that has a yard for me to sunbath in, and has another dog for me to wrestle with. I am my foster family's first large foster, and they joke about how I'm the perfect 'gateway big-foster' dog. My foster family doesn't have cats nor children, so they are not sure how I will do, but based on my temperament they think I will be ok.

Laila is a Female Pit Bull Mix that we estimate to be around 3 years old and weighs 45 lbs.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Hi, I'm Fido. More information on me coming soon!

Animal Rescue of the Rockies believes that every pet should find a wonderful, caring home. To ensure each pet finds the best possible home, we ask that you fill out our Adoption Application so we can learn more about you and your household. We review each application we receive and will contact you within 48 hours. If your home sounds like a good match for you and the pet,

the next step is to set up a "meet and greet." After meeting the pet, if you would like to proceed with adopting, we'll ask that you read and sign our Adoption Agreement and pay the adoption fee. Our adoption fees help cover the costs of saving more lives!

A home visit will be scheduled within one week of your new pet going home with you.

The adoption fee for this pet is $395 and includes a $50 training deposit. Our adoption fee covers the following:

- Spay/Neuter, Microchip

- DAPP vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for all DAPP boosters after adoption.

- Rabies vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for any rabies vaccinations after adoption.

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an adoption application by clicking

here

.

We want our pets to go to a lifelong new home, so thank you for your patience during the adoption process!

Please email ARRColorado@gmail.com for more information, as we can not accept calls at this time.

Our adoption process is:

1. Fill out our Adoption Application online. We'll contact you within 48 hours to answer any questions you may have about the pet.

2. If the pet looks like a great match, we'll schedule a meet and greet and ask you to fill out our online Adoption Agreement if you'd like to proceed with adopting. Once you've completed the Adoption Agreement and pay the pet's Adoption Fee, you can arrange to pick up your new furry family member!

animal.description:
Check out this handsome boy! Meet Kodiak! ?

"Kodiak is our little observer. He tends to hang back and watch everything that is going on. Once he has deemed everything good to go, he will happily pounce on one of his siblings and play. You can tell that this boy is smart and I swear he seems to have a "thinking face" on sometimes. He does have a more laid-back temperament compared to his siblings. He also seems to be a bit more independent."

Kodiak is a 6 week old male Great Pyrenees mix. He currently weighs about 10lbs. Our best guess is he will top out somewhere in the 80-90lb range.

-Kodiak has been with us since birth. His mom Varity came to us heavily pregnant. We are unsure of who his dad was. Varity's former owner believes it was a male Pyr mix who visits sometimes but doesn't know for sure.

-Kodiak is still a baby. This means his new family needs to be ready to potty train him, work with him on basic manners, and have a lot of time on their hands to help raise him.

-Kodiak will need proper socialization. His new family will need to expose him to a little bit of everything. Such as walks, car rides, public outings, visitors, other dogs, etc.

-Kodiak will not be ready to go home until February 22, give or take a couple of days. Anyone applying to adopt him needs to be able to bring him home close to that date.

-Kodiak is being fostered in Kiowa, OK. We do not send our dogs on transports or ship them. This means his new family needs to pick him up, even if they are out of state.

Well, you made it this far. Time for the big question? Will Kodiak be your newest family member? If so, you can apply to adopt him at https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app

His adoption fee is $275. That includes two sets of puppy shots, bordetella, and rabies. He will be micro-chipped, have a fecal done, be de-wormed, be spayed/neutered, and will be current on my heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

Dante is said the be house trained. He will sit when told and is great on leash. He hopes he can turn his frown upside down and find a new home very soon. It would be best if Dante was an only pet and he has not been around kids. He is current on vaccines, neutered, micro-chipped and tested negative for heart worms. Dante is waiting to meet you in run 827 and his ID# is 627121. 
 Please note, all of the pet listings on Friends of Shelter Animals for Cobb are done by volunteers, not shelter staff. If this pet came in as lost (not an owner surrender), we don't know how they might be with children, other pets, or if house trained. You can bring your pet to the shelter for a meet & greet with your potential new best friend. Brody is a super sweet big boy. He's quiet and about medium on the energy scale. He's good with dogs and visual cat test showed no reaction. Kid test went really well.Thank you for your interest in adopting a pet from Guardians of the Green Mile Inc. We are a group of individuals that have come together to save the lives of animals that are in danger of being euthanized. We raise funds to fully vet the animals and to provide them with a stable home until they are adopted. All of the dogs in our Rescue are in Foster homes while they are looking for their forever family. The only time we put a dog in boarding is for a Foster to go on vacation if another Foster is not able to care for them. We appreciate your taking the time to fill out the application to adopt one of our Guardians of the Green Mile pets. The questions that we ask are to only find the right fit for all of our dogs and the families that will be adopting them. Adoption donation is $300.00 for dogs over 1 year old and $350 with a $50.00 spay / neuter deposit for puppies/dogs under 1 year old.

Click on this link to access the online form, https://www.jotform.us/form/43196636952162

animal.description:
Smokey is about 14 months old, and he is a pretty amazing guy. He's part Lab, part Pittie, and part German Shepherd, with the best qualities of all three breeds.
Housebroken, walks great on a leash, loves going for rides. Would do great in a home with kids over 6 years, as he is a big dog (70 pounds) with a lot of happy energy.
He does okay with other dogs when introduced in a calm situation but we don't recommend him for the dog park, where there are a lot of loose dogs. NO cats, please. All of our dogs are available for a $200 donation. This includes them being spayed/neutered, micro-chipped, and fully vaccinated.
To adopt a dog, we require an approved pre-application, as well as a securely fenced yard. This means an actual, physical, fence. 'Invisible' fences are not acceptable, sorry. If you live in an apartment and do not have a yard, we are not able to adopt to you.
Please contact us at: dogtownmutts@gmail.com for details.
Please note: we typically do not do 'out of the area' adoptions. This would be any location more than 60 miles away from the Reno/Carson City area.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Hi, I'm Raiden. More information on me coming soon!

Animal Rescue of the Rockies believes that every pet should find a wonderful, caring home. To ensure each pet finds the best possible home, we ask that you fill out our Adoption Application so we can learn more about you and your household. We review each application we receive and will contact you within 48 hours. If your home sounds like a good match for you and the pet,

the next step is to set up a "meet and greet." After meeting the pet, if you would like to proceed with adopting, we'll ask that you read and sign our Adoption Agreement and pay the adoption fee. Our adoption fees help cover the costs of saving more lives!

A home visit will be scheduled within one week of your new pet going home with you.

The adoption fee for this pet is $345. Our adoption fee covers the following:

- Spay/Neuter, Microchip

- DAPP vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for all DAPP boosters after adoption.

- Rabies vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for any rabies vaccinations after adoption.

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an adoption application by clicking

here

.

We want our pets to go to a lifelong new home, so thank you for your patience during the adoption process!

Please email ARRColorado@gmail.com for more information, as we can not accept calls at this time.

Our adoption process is:

1. Fill out our Adoption Application online. We'll contact you within 48 hours to answer any questions you may have about the pet.

2. If the pet looks like a great match, we'll schedule a meet and greet and ask you to fill out our online Adoption Agreement if you'd like to proceed with adopting. Once you've completed the Adoption Agreement and pay the pet's Adoption Fee, you can arrange to pick up your new furry family member!

animal.description: Roses are red, my eyes are blue, getting adopted will be a dream come true! I am about 35 pounds and I just turned one on January 22nd! I was rescued from Cleveland, TX where I was living in an outdoor kennel. I am catching onto house manners very quickly. I really enjoy being outside. Minus ten degrees? No problem! Ive had a few accidents but never in my kennel, I dont mark in the house, and Im always excited to go outside to potty and sniff around. My foster mom said Ill be neutered soon. I dont know what that is, but it sounds like fun! Speaking of fun, plush toys, rope toys, and balls are my favorite, and I especially like playing with my resident dog sister. We play hard and nap harder. I even have resident chihuahua brothers, but theyre not as fun and we ignore each other. I love to be pet and am good with older kids. I havent been tested with younger children yet, but my foster mom thinks I will be just fine with the proper introduction. She says I dont have a mean bone in my body. If you have room in your heart and home for me, please fill out an adoption application ASAP! I cant wait to meet you! Brocks adoption fee is $375 which covers his neuter, vaccinations, microchip and any additional medical care he may have needed while in the rescues care. We are a foster based rescue, we do not house dogs at a facility. Age and breed, are NLR's best guess as we often don't know who or what mom and dad are. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website www.northernlakesrescue.org

animal.description: Hello my name is Duke also known as Dukers from my foster mama. This cold weather thing is still new to me, but I love all the new scents when we go outside! Im around 2 years old and a big boy at 72 pounds and could stand to gain a few My foster family consists of another dog who is a little bigger than me who I'm really starting to like, I'm trying to win her over with my charm. There are also 2 cats, who I've been very good with so far; however, I am curious of the one when he moves fast. And they have this tiny human who is loud and moves a lot. He's great to give kisses to, and I really don't mind him, he gives good hugs and pets. My favorite thing is to be loved and get pets and attention! I'm a really good kisser and give you my paw so I can pet you back. Overall, I'm a very calm, content guy who's looking for my furever family so I can show them how much love I have to give. I know how to sit, shake and haven't had any inside accidents yet! I really don't like slippery laminate floors, the ones here scare me at times, but if I walk on them I get to spend time next to my foster family which is where I like to be. I'm ok alone at times with music playing softly and a nice blanket to curl up on, that way I can relax and nap until I join my foster family again in the mornings or when they get home from work. I'm not much of a barker so far unless I'm scared and don't wanna be alone. I get nervous in new areas and freeze at times, but with reassurance I can do anything. Dukes's adoption fee is $375 which covers his neuter, vaccinations, microchip and any additional medical care he may have needed while in the rescues care. We are a foster based rescue, we do not house dogs at a facility. Age and breed, are NLR's best guess as we often don't know who or what mom and dad are. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website www.northernlakesrescue.org

animal.description:
Hello, I’m “Annie”!
   I am sweet older girl at 12 years old and only 5 pounds. I am a Yorkie (with maybe a little Maltese mixed in!) and I have the softest white fur. 
  You may have noticed my eyes are a bit cloudy, I am mostly blind but it doesn’t slow me down! I have done a pretty good job of learning my way around my foster house. I also do a great job of using my puppy pads since I prefer to use those instead of going outside in the cold! 
  Sudden movements tend to startle me but I’m friends with everyone! I’m fostered with other small dogs as well as children and we get along just fine. 
  My favorite thing in the world is snuggling with my foster family on the couch under a soft blanket. 
  If you have a quiet spot in your home for a sweet older girl like me, I’d love to meet you!! My adoption fee is $150.00.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
Daisy is available to adopt in the Chicagoland area, and is being fostered in a home. Appointments to visit her will be set up for approved adopters only. Adoption fee is $350 which includes all age appropriate vaccines and she is already microchipped. Her adoptive family will be required to spay her by the age of 6 months. Please visit our website at http://newstartdogrescue.org and fill out an application if you are interested.

Daisy is a high energy shepherd catahoula mix puppy 17 weeks old, 22 lbs.  She is a very sweet and loving puppy that loves to play in the snow and chase her toys.  She already likes to bring them back as well.  Daisy loves to snuggle too! She is still working on potty training, and getting better every day!  She is wonderful with kids but should be watched as she has a lot of puppy energy.  She is probably going to grow to at least 50 - 70 lbs judging by her giant paws. She sleeps through most of the night so long as you give her one quick potty break outside half way through.  

Daisy’s forever home should:
-Have a full, physical fenced yard
-a single family home (no apartments, please)
-No young children under 8. 
-Working breed experience. Both Shepherd’s and Catahoulas are protective breeds that need training and a task to do in order to thrive.

animal.description:
** as of 1/1/21 @ 1pm we are no longer accepting applications for miss Roxie. ** 

If you have already submitted a request, please be patient as we work through all of the inquiry’s for both her and her puppies. We will be calling everyone by Friday morning. We won’t have the opportunity to get back to everyone that has applied, but if you do not get a phone call by Friday morning, we have move forward with another applicant. 
Be aware we get dogs/puppies in frequently, some that don’t make it to this site. You’re welcome to send an application request with the breed/age/gender you’re looking for to have us hold.  

If you’re looking for a well rounded, loving companion without going through the hassle of puppy stages, look no further.  Roxie came to us with 8 puppies in tow, after being found in an abandoned house. Now that her crew is nearing adoption day, we would like to get a home lined up for her! She has been a wonderful momma, and has captured the hearts of everyone she meets. Roxie has a kind, patient heart and spends her free time snuggled up with the young kids in her foster home. She gets along with dogs of all sizes, and while she can live with a cat, she will chase them. The second you meet this girl, you won’t want to let her go. She is just under 40 pounds, and thinks she’s a lap dog! She is great on the leash and loves to go for walks, and is all around a mellow girl who is up for whatever is in store for the day. She is fully house trained, knows all basic commands, and non destructive. She is believed to be 6 years old, and will be fully vaccinated/microchipped and spayed upon adoption.  Please email if you’re interested in finding out more or adopting Roxie.

animal.description:
This handsome guy is super happy and outgoing with adults but he does not prefer the company of children.  Maybe he wasn't exposed to them when he was younger, or maybe he was treated poorly by children and is no longer comfortable with them.  Whatever the reason, his previous owner indicated he did not like children and we will make sure he is placed appropriately in a home with no kids.

Now for the wonderful things about Loki .... He is good with other dogs and good with cats!  He is great in the car and really enjoys going for a ride.  He is housebroken and good on a leash.  He enjoys playing fetch (must be the retriever in him) and loves his chew toys.   

At just 1 year old Loki is young and active and would enjoy a home where he gets plenty of exercise, attention, training and love.  He is very happy and outgoing and will make someone a great companion.

PLEASE NOTE:    DO NOT CALL THE SHELTER.  If you have questions you will get a much faster response if you email questions to  HSPCdogs@gmail.com 
 
If you rent you must verify with your landlord that they allow dogs and do not have any breed or size restrictions.

We are open for adoptions Thursday - Saturday from 12-4pm (excluding holidays).  Adoptions are on a first come, first serve basis.  Adoption fee is $100 (cash or check only, NO credit cards).   Meet and greets with kids and other dogs are required.

animal.description:
Nellie is about 4 years old. Nellie is VERY shy at first and is going to need someone who is patient and understanding with her and willing to give her lots of time to get used to you and her new environment. We recommend a person with shy dog experience or are very dog-savvy! She would do best in a quiet household where there is not much commotion and no children as well as a SLOW transition into your life. Because of that, we ask that she stays local to Temecula and surrounding cities so we can easily assist when needed. 

Now, about her personality...
Nellie is a VERY sweet girl who will follow you around like a shadow. She gets very excited to see her people. She loves to get lots of attention from you too. She is 100% house trained. She appears to be okay with cats. She prefers mature male dogs over females and exuberant puppies but will also do just perfectly fine living in a single dog home. Nellie recently had orthopedic surgery so she cannot do strenuous exercise or hiking - at least not yet. Nellie is pretty mellow but does enjoy playing a little bit every now and then. She would really appreciate having a family who is enthusiastic about continuing her socialization and help her explore the outside world.

If interested in ADOPTING, please fill out an adoption application online:
www.hoperanchanimalsanctuary.org/adoption-application

A copy of your application can be sent to us via email

For more information about Nellie, please contact Kathy:
Call/Text: (951) 515-4077
Email: k.haley.hope.ranch@gmail.com

animal.description:
Sophia is a gorgeous, affectionate Red Nose Pittie who is 2 years old and weighs 65 lbs.  Her foster family says she is a "one of a kind" special girl who has it ALL!  She is great with other dogs and LOVES kids of all ages!  She is a happy, gentle, social dog who is maternal, calm and a shining example of the Pitbull as a Nanny dog!  She is a snuggly, intelligent, obedient girl who loves all humans and is extremely nurturing & gentle with babies & kids of all ages (she is currently in a foster home with 2 beautiful boys ages 10 & 8 months).  It is obvious that Sophia has had several litters of pups and possesses a motherly instinct that allows her to gravitate naturally towards kids. She naps when they nap, she dotes on them when they're awake!  She is a low/medium energy dog that does not require much maintenance except snuggles. She loves to give kisses!!   She will happily go in her crate if she wants some peace & quiet, but more often than not she wants to be close to her humans.  She is still learning basic commands such as sit & lay down, but she is a quick learner, walks well on a leash, and loves car rides! This amazing girl will fit into ANY home!!!  She is spayed, fully vaccinated, microchipped, crate trained and 100% housebroken (if she needs to go out, she will stand by the door and if that doesn't get your attention, she will start whining at the door).

Sophia has her own Facebook page because she is THAT special! If you want to see more pics of her at her current foster home, please go to The Foster Pupperz Diaries by copying the link below into your browser:  
https://www.facebook.com/108715817262756/posts/275862293881440/

For more information about Sophia, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt this sweet girl, please submit an application for her at https://www.barkvilledogrescue.org/applications

animal.description: Tyga is an American rap singer and one of his songs says, I'm best . . . I'm blessed. Pasadena Humane's Tyga isn't a rapper, but he did cry when his owner moved away and left him at the shelter. He had lived his entire life with that owner and now at age 13, he finds himself without a home. Looking at his picture, one can see an obviously well cared for dog with good looks on top of it all! He is described by staff as calm and getting adjusted to his surroundings. His owner reported that he is an indoor dog and that he is house-trained. He is good with people and also good with kids. However, he doesn't really like the mail carrier much, but then, how many dogs do? He knows his sit command cue. Volunteers report that he enjoys getting petted, plays with a ball, and that he walks well on leash. His age qualifies him for our Senior for Seniors Program in which any adopter who is sixty years old or more can adopt Tyga completely free! Yes, he's a bit stiff in his joints, but that means he's all the more in need of a warm and loving home. Tyga needs to feel blessed again and with someone who thinks he's the best! Learn more about our virtual adoption process .

animal.description:
This beautiful girl has been in rescue for over 100 days. We figured it was long past due for some new photos and bio! Without further ado, say hello to She'! ?

"She' is a smiler. She LOVES to smile and always seems to be happy. She wants to be close to you and will happily lie on the couch with you. Other times she will be by your feet. She is also the kind of girl who would probably sleep in bed with her new owners if given the choice. She' has the cutest little freckles on her nose and the most beautiful patch of color on her face. She' is all about having fun! She loves exploring the yard outside, she loves to play with the other dogs, she loves chewing on her bones, and she loves getting to be part of the family! If you are looking for a playful and super sweet dog, this girl will steal your heart ? "

She's is a 3-year-old female Great Pyrenees. She currently weighs around 80lbs. She' is a happy girl and does well when meeting new people. She has not had much experience being out in public. So when she sees another dog she does try to go greet it and sometimes gets overexcited. Unless her new owner is experienced with large dogs, they should probably skip the walks around the neighborhood with this girl. However, she would probably LOVE going for hikes/walks in more secluded areas where she can't get distracted by other dogs walking around. She' has not been destructive in her foster home. She has only chewed on bones. She' has not shown to have any issues with resource guarding in her foster home. She' doesn't really jump on people, but sometimes does if she is really excited. She' does ride well in the car, but can sometimes be vocal if she sees something that interests her outside. She' does walk well on a leash given there are no distractions that make her want to stray from her course ?

She' has a more energetic personality. She is laid back inside and typically just grabs a bone to chew on. Sometimes she will play with the other dogs. When outside, she loves playing chase with them and exploring. She' has not shown any interest in playing fetch. We are unsure at this time if she is a water dog or not. We are unsure how She' would do in an apartment setting. She' can be vocal if there is reason to be (another dog is barking/strange noise/stranger/etc). When no one is home, She' has free run of the house and does great. At night, she tends to sleep downstairs on the couch or doggie bed. She' is potty trained. Her foster does not kennel, though.

She' is one gorgeous girl. You could definitely describe her as the life of the party. If she sounds like your kind of girl, here are a few more things to note before applying for her

-She' is an alpha dog. If another dog challenges her, she won't back down. It would be best if her new home had a submissive male dog that likes to play.

-She' is good with cats. She doesn't seem to pay them any mind in her foster home.

-She' has not been around any kids. She does have a super sweet temperament but can be rowdy at times. We recommend the kids be 8+ in her new home.

-She' is good with other dogs, but she is food aggressive towards them. She does need to be fed separately from them. She hasn't shown to have any treat aggression, but those interactions should always be monitored as well(if there are other dogs around). When no food is around you will see her playing tug-o-war with them or roughhousing in the backyard. She does enjoy their companionship.

-She' would be fine as an only dog if her new family was home most of the day. They would also need to be on the active side.

She' has been waiting a while for her PYRfect home. She may not be a dog for everyone, but she will be the best addition to the right family! One that is looking for a goofy, smiley, and super lovable girl! If you happen to be that family, please apply for her at https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app

Her adoption fee is $225. That includes DHLPP, Rabies, and Bordatella shots. She will be micro-chipped, heart-worm tested, have a fecal done, be de-wormed, be spayed/neutered, and will be current on heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

Ideal home: Cocoa is a pretty adaptable pup! She'd love an adopter that is eager to work on training so she can learn all the best behaviors.

And she gives you the weirdest, cute smile when you hit the spots right. While Cocoa is great at loving you, she is also able to be alone in the crate or be a quiet work from home buddy self-soothing. If you want a girl who loves to lick your face, is smart, often wants rubs and snuggles then look no further than Cocoa because she is a full package.

Cocoa's adoption fee is 300. She is spayed, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. She will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense.

animal.description:
Sweet Charmer is a 14-16(!) year-old shepherd hound mix who came to us from another rescue in the Miami area. We are looking for a hospice foster home for him - Canine Estates will take care of his medical expenses at our local vet(Palm Harbor, FL), and all he needs is love and a place to lay his head for the rest of his days. If you do not live in the immediate area for vet visits, he is available as a traditional adoption as well. He has arthritis and balance issues, but still manages to get around pretty well for his age. He also has a heart murmur and needs his ears cleaned regularly, but otherwise is a sweet, healthy old man. Very food motivated and a nap lover, he will also get along with one or two mellow dogs if they are not too rambunctious or in his face. Cats and children would likely be fine as well. He does not walk well on a leash and cannot handle steps very well, so we would require a single-story home with a fenced yard for him to sunbathe in. Do you have room in your home and heart for this old man?

Please fill out an application and we will call you once approved to set up a meet and greet. If you have any questions, email director@canineestates.com or call 727-412-0558

animal.description:
My name is Alvin. I am a shy but very sweet 53 lbs,1 year old black lab. I am full grown, but I might still need to fill out a little more. When I first meet my new family I will be nervous, especially after traveling for three days and having to learn a whole new routine with new people. It will take me about 3-4 weeks to really warm up and show you how much fun I can really be. I do best with considerate children over 6 years old. It would be best for me to go to a family with no other dogs and no cats. I will need a family that is patient, willing to spend time with me and ready to love me. My life in Texas has been a hard life. I was dumped out in the country and had to be trapped in order to be rescued. I get nervous meeting new people, but my foster mom has really worked with me. She keeps me well socialized and it has really helped me come out of my shell. I walk well on a leash and enjoy going for walks. I do best when provided with stimulating toys to keep me busy. I love my Kong. Some good activities for me are walks, hikes, going out to eat at pet friendly establishments or other fun activities you enjoy doing. I need a home with a fully secure wooden fenced backyard. 

He is up to date on vaccines according to his age, he has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer. He is microchipped, neutered, comes with 6 months of preventatives, one month free trial of pet insurance, and all of our animals receive a health certificate (this states a licensed veterinary saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, it is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and transport is included in adoption fee of $500!

He is currently being fostered in Houston, TX but will be traveling to the PNW as soon as he finds his/her perfect home!

For questions, please email krissa@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

To apply: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/26841/generic

animal.description:
Hello adventure seekers! Meet Maximillion-- the most handsome, well behaved, well rounded husky that is ready to join you on all of your outdoor adventures! Just look at that smile! He is a big, fluffy boy estimated at 7 years old and weighs in at approximately 85 lbs. He's big and strong and ready for any challenge you send his way!

Max is kennel trained, potty trained, good with people, kids and dogs! He's a little too interested in cats...and squirrels! Will have to say he will not do well in a home with cats. Max knows how to sit, shake, loooves car rides, walks well on a leash but he is a strong boy and if he something tickles his nose he will pull in that direction. He likes to take in all of the smells. He is not very interested in other dogs or people, which makes it so much easier for walks. His current foster takes him along on his daily jogs, which he loves. His foster momma and kiddos also walk him and he does well. Max takes treats very gently, loads into a car easily and is super mindful in general. He understands the word "no" very well! This big guy will make such an amazing companion to anyone that is ready for some fun!

He arrives in the PNW on 2/9. Don't miss out on such a great catch-- please apply here- https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/30275/generic

or email cynthia@threelittlepittiesrescue.org if you have an application on file.

The adoption fee is $550 and includes all vaccines (DHPP & booster, Bordatella, Rabies), spay/neuter, microchip, multiple dewormings, flea and heartworm preventative with 6 month of heartworm preventative injection for after adoption, a high quality nylon Martingale collar, a 30 day trial of pet insurance, transport from TX to the PNW, and many years of priceless memories.
