animal.description:
Ziggy is a gorgeous dog with a lush white coat, a wagging tail, and a happy smile. He is a middle-aged gent (7 years old/50 lbs), who has been professionally trained.

Not your average dog, Ziggy is our 'unicorn' who when he loves, loves with his whole heart.

Ziggy will need slow introductions to new people especially in his home.
and he likes to be the protector of his person/people, so it's always necessary he be put in another room when new people enter the home. 

Ziggs takes time to warm up to new people, although he can sometimes make a snap judgment that yes, you're his kind of people and it's love at first sight. Ziggs loves his walks, is housetrained, is wonderfully 

affectionate with 'his' people, loves to play fetch (he's a pro), and can also amuse himself for hours playing with a ball or two or four! A good roll in the grass, a belly rub, showing off his sit, paw, and down for a treat, he's pretty amazing

. Ziggy loves a car ride, and often goes for a ride with staff for a bagel! Well behaved when home alone, 

As stated. once he decides he loves you, his love has no boundaries! Ziggy also needs slow introductions to other dogs, but at this stage in his life, he's fine being solo. Our Ziggs is ready to find the person to devote his life to; he's neutered, up to date with vaccinations, microchipped.

Ziggy is neutered, up to date on his vaccinations, microchipped and ready to find his person to devote his life to

animal.description:
Cleo was found on the street like many of our rescues. She is now safe with her foster family. Cleo loves to play and cuddle with her doggy foster brothers and her foster sister. 

Location: Houston, TX

IN-STATE ADOPTION ONLY 

If you’re interested in meeting this cutie please fill out an adoption application:

https://loveandrescue.com/adopt/

Please ONLY call the number listed on our page if you HAVE filled out an adoption application. 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Love And Rescue Adoption Requirements:

All interested adopters must have/understand ALL of the following before being considered as a potential adopter. We take placing an animal's life in your hands very seriously and want to ensure we are doing the best thing for both the animal and for you.

- Valid Drivers License
- Be over the age of 23
- Renters must show proof or provide information to verify that the pet is allowed at the residence
- Be willing to have an in-person interview to go over expectations for both you and the animal
- Be willing to have a Love And Rescue volunteer do a home visit
- Dog Adoption Fee: $150 / Cat Adoption Fee: $75
- MUST FILL OUT THE LOVE AND RESCUE ADOPTION APPLICATION (Link below)

https://loveandrescue.com/adopt/

animal.description:
Meet Janie!

Janie came to us recently when her disabled owner was unable to properly care for her. She lived in an apartment with an owner that never left.

She is said to be a chocolate lab and Australian shepherd mix, but definitely exudes more of the herding temperament and has alot of energy! 
Janie is about 11 months old and 56lb. 
Janie needs somebody that will be home a lot right now that can work with her departure anxiety. She sleeps great in a crate all night long without any issues. A doggie brother or sister must be young and patient enough to handle playing and jumping on one another since she is still an big puppy and doesnt know her boundaries. BUT she LOVES dogs and playing and is also good with cats. She is great with kids but again may jump/needs continued manners work.
She is crate and potty trained and knows sit and paw, but will need some continued training on the leash. She loves to run and would make a great running partner. But again she did live in apartment.
Due to the need for continued manners work we require no kids under 10 but she does love kids and everyone she meets. She has not been cat tested.

Adoption fee is $300 and includes spay/neuter, microchip, fecal/deworming, vaccines and prevention up to date. Ohio residents only.

STS is a foster-based and volunteer-run rescue. We do not have a physical location or set hours for you to meet dogs, and it does take time to answer each inquiry. All dogs are in foster homes and once an application is approved and a home visit is completed you will be able to schedule meet and greets with available dogs. We encourage interested individuals to get approved prior to searching as it helps expedite the process. A Petfinder inquiry is not a substitute for an application. For detailed information about our adoption process, including fees, please visit our website at http://www.stopthesuffering.org.

animal.description:
Noah is a 2 yr old, 55 lb,black and tan Rottie/ Coonhound mix. He is a recent arrival from Texas. His foster mom says, "he is a sweet boy that wants to be your partner and get loved on. He is leash, crate and house trained. He likes cow hooves to chew on. He barks to alert. He is good with dogs of all sizes. He is submissive and cowers and screams if another dog is aggressive. He will crouch and show you his belly when meeting. He is not food aggressive. He tried to be the co pilot when he's riding in a car." Noah would like a family that likes to walk and let his roam the great outdoors with them, camping or hiking. He'll make a great family companion. 

The adoption fee is $300 and covers age appropriate vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter.

 Applications are typically worked in time stamp order based on date/time of submission. If you have other dogs in your home, they must all meet the potential adoptee. It may save you a trip to bring them with you when you visit, if you are certain you want to adopt a new family member. 

*****We are currently operating by appointment only during the social distancing stage of quarantine. If you want to meet this pet, or are interested in adopting, please submit an inquiry or email to email@townandcountryhumanesociety.org.

Someone from the rescue will contact you and/or your family and determine, on a broad level, whether you might be a fit for the animal. If so, they will provide instructions for completing the application. Your application will be reviewed and you will be contacted to set up a time to meet at the shelter or the foster home. The introduction between you and the pet will be supervised by one of the dog counselors or the foster. If all goes well, you can adopt during the same visit.

Please be sure to follow us on Facebook to learn more about Town and Country Humane Society and our mission.

animal.description:
0121013 - Hi my names Ainsley! Im a 10mo old lab mix and Im looking for my furever home! Some of my favorite things include playing with my foster doggy sisters, frolicking outside in the snow, and any kind of toy - squeaky, chewy, bouncy, I really mean ANY toy! Sometimes I mistake human things (like shoes or socks) for dog toys but I quickly learn if you tell me no. Ive been able to entertain myself for hours with just a bin of various toys!

My foster parents think that Id be best suited in a home with another dog or dogs who can help bring me out of my shell. I have a hidden curious, playful nature but only after I get comfortable. I definitely need a patient family who will put in the time to build my trust because I can be apprehensive towards humans. I dont like to be cornered or corralled, so Im probably not best for a family with young children. Despite my timidness when I first meet you, when I warm up to you I am pretty much the perfect dog! 

I can sleep either in a kennel or in bed with you, but if its my choice Id always choose the bed! Im working on my commands sit and come and with some more time I could really master these. Im not overly food motivated but positive praise from humans works as a good alternative for me. I am nearly completely potty trained, and frequent opportunities to go outside really help me with this. I am a natural leash walker and will stay right by your side without any pulling! To adopt me please complete an application at www.sloppykisses.org/adoptions!

animal.description:
Shellie is in a foster home, and is currently not at the shelter. Please find info on how to adopt her below, thanks!



Shellie is a sweet and gorgeous girl with an innocently dopey smile that will warm your heart. She's calm, friendly and enjoys spending time with her human. Shellie is very polite, doesn't bark and prefers pets and cuddling over play. She is well-behaved but would benefit from some house training. Shellie doesn't need a lot of space and will do well in house or apartment setting. She has a calm temperament and may do well with other pet siblings, pending meetup.



Shellie enjoys her slow walks a lot and is always excited to go out, but due to a health condition should not exert herself too much, or be allowed to overheat. Medical records will be shared with those who apply.



Shelly would thrive in a quiet home where she can get the care she needs and have lots of cuddle time!



HOW TO ADOPT - Please fill out a Dog Adoption Application, available at http://www.seattle.gov/animalshelter/forms.htm and email it to the Seattle Animal Shelter Foster Dog Program at adoptionreview@gmail.com.



IMPORTANT NOTE: Many of our dogs will receive numerous applications, and the Seattle Animal Shelter asks for your patience during the process of finding the very best match. If you have questions about this dog that have not been answered above, please contact us at sasfosterdogs@gmail.com. If you would like to arrange to meet this dog, you must submit an adoption application. Thank you!

animal.description:
Sweet and handsome Jazzy Blue came into rescue because his owner knew she could no longer care for him. There were tears all around, but everyone knew Jazzy would find a great new home. A typical wiggle-butt Aussie, Jazzy is a 4 1/2-year-old gorgeous blue merle. Hes so Velcro that hell do whatever his person is doing. He loves adventures and needs an active family to keep him moving. Hes a whopping 89 pounds so an energetic family will keep this loving boy healthy and happy.

Jazzy loves walks and is good on a leash. He enjoys car rides and anything his person wants to do. He is 100% housetrained and is crate trained, but is totally trustworthy in the home. He is a quick learner and knows sit, down, leave it, and has great recall. Hes eager to please and obviously loves treats!

He is great with the many dogs in his foster home and would be good with or without another dog. The main requirement says his foster mom, who is utterly smitten with this great guy, is that he spend forever in an amazing place with amazing people.

Jazzy Blue is up to date on vaccinations, neutered, microchipped, and current on heartworm/flea and tick prevention. Also included in his adoption is a Fi GPS collar and one year of GPS service subscription. If he were to escape, as soon as he leaves the safe zone you set around your home, you are alerted
so that you can find Jazzy's whereabouts. Youll also be able to see how many steps per day he takes to ensure he gets the right amount of exercise, alongside many other features to explore in the Fi mobile app.

animal.description:
Hi, I’m Lily, but I’m no delicate flower--I’m one tough little girl! I’m an eight-pound, eight-year-old female chihuahua, fully vetted, vaccinated, spayed, microchipped, and on heartworm preventative. I’ve had a rough couple of months and now I’m ready to live the good life with my forever family. Could that be you?

I was given up by my previous owner, who was older and unable to take care of me. When I came to my foster family, I was in a lot of pain. The vet said I had a bladder infection and I had to have surgery to remove twelve bladder stones. I wasn’t so sure about it, but now I feel like a whole new dog! 

Now that I’m healthy, I am very active and love to run, jump, and play, then go crashing into my doggy friends! I’m a sociable girl, and I get along just fine with the other three chihuahuas, the cat, and the toddler in my foster home. And now that the bladder infection is gone, my housetraining is on point! I always let my foster mom know when I need to go. I must confess that I’m a bit of a food critic. If you serve me dry food, I will turn up my nose and demand something a little more appealing! What can I say? I know what I like!

I think I deserve a comfortable home and loving family after what I’ve been through, don’t you? If you’re ready for some fierce fun with a feisty pup, look no further! Fill out that application today!

Lily’s adoption fee is $250. If you are interested in adopting Lily, please DO NOT SEND A MESSAGE TO OUR RESCUE GROUP.  We are too busy placing dogs in great homes to answer messages and inquiries through the listing site. 

PLEASE GO TO THE LINK BELOW TO COMPLETE AN ADOPTION APPLICATION.
 
www.chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application
 
CRT requires an approved adoption application and a home visit for all adoption applicants.  CRT transports to OH, KY, IL, MI, MN, WI.

Thank you for your interest in adopting a pet from Guardians of the Green Mile Inc. We are a group of individuals that have come together to save the lives of animals that are in danger of being euthanized. We raise funds to fully vet the animals and to provide them with a stable home until they are adopted. All of the dogs in our Rescue are in Foster homes while they are looking for their forever family. The only time we put a dog in boarding is for a Foster to go on vacation if another Foster is not able to care for them. We appreciate your taking the time to fill out the application to adopt one of our Guardians of the Green Mile pets. The questions that we ask are to only find the right fit for all of our dogs and the families that will be adopting them. Adoption donation is $300.00 for dogs over 1 year old and $350 with a $50.00 spay / neuter deposit for puppies/dogs under 1 year old.

animal.description:
Chase is a 7-year-old golden boy looking for a patient and kind forever home. Chase struggles with some fear-based behavior. He arrived with some guarding behavior, mostly related to his food and his crate. He is learning to trust his foster family and is improving every day. Chase is highly intelligent and is responding very well to patient, positive reinforcement. His food aggression is disappearing and he is learning that his crate is a safe place.

Chase will need an experienced, dog savvy home that provide him with a loving environment where he can live without anxiety and fear. Chase will need ongoing reinforcement of his training to thrive.

Chase gets along great with cats and other dogs! He would benefit from a confident sibling to help him learn how to be a "dog!"

Chase likes children, however, he is best suited for an adult-only home.

If you feel you would be well suited to Chase, please email us at applications@grrswf.org for an adoption application.

animal.description:
Please contact C.A.R.E. for more information about this pet. Bombay American Staffordshire Terrier, Born in 2019, Neutered male Hello there! I'm Bombay, and I am a real stunner. My super-shiny, soft, silver coat almost looks like chrome. When you meet me, you'll notice that my incredibly charming happy-go-lucky personality matches my handsome looks. I absolutely love affection, giving kissing and I especially enjoy pets and belly rubs. Toys are so much fun. I really adore soft stuffed toys to chase and sliding across the floor being silly and puppy like! I do walk well on leash, but sometimes I get awfully excited when I see small animals and can really show my strength. That's why my ideal home would be with a very strong handler and someone that is willing to work with me on this. I'm great at the "sit" command, and I take treats very gently. I'll admit that sometimes I have a tendency to jump up for attention, but I also respond well to correction because all I want to do is please. I've been told by my volunteer friends that I am a perfect gentleman with impeccable manners. If you are looking for a super-affectionate, energetic, fun companion, I'm right here waiting for you.
Adoption Information: Size: Extra Large/weighs 82 pounds Children: 10 and up (due to size and strength) Dogs: Selective Cats: NoRequired: Single-family home with fenced in yard Experience: Needs a strong and dog savvy, experienced handler. Not the dog for a first-time dog family. Plus must live in a house, no apartment or condo living for him.Adoption fee: $300 This dog is neutered, microchipped and has had a full veterinary checkup and vaccines.
If you are interested in more information or would like to meet this dog, please fill out our online adoption survey: carenorthshore.org/dog-adoption-survey

Meet Angel!

Angel is 10 years old and a super snuggler. Sadly, she is actually one half of a bonded pair who have had a very hard life. Over the past few years they’ve been bounced around from shelter to shelter. Evidently their owner was unable to maintain a housing situation. At one point, the dogs were abandoned in a car with nothing but water for four days. The last picture we have posted is of her male companion dog with her.

Angel is a sweet, sweet girl. She has some mobility issues, related to arthritis. She is a little stiff to get up or down and stairs are definitely a challenge for her. She limps just a bit on her front left leg and really only needs very slow, short walks to be happy. 

We think both dogs deserve to live a comfortable, safe life from here on out.

Adoption Process: We are not first come first served. Indigo Rescue focuses on finding good matches between dogs and families to ensure life long adoptions. We deliver all dogs to their new homes. All of our dogs are in foster homes. 

If you’re interested in meeting one of our dogs, please use the following link and complete our Adoption Application. You can either scan your completed application and email it to us at: info@indigorescue.org, or you can fax it to us at: 888-502-7660.
The link is not live, so you will need to copy and paste it into your browser: https://storage.googleapis.com/gator-users/user-680788/documents/d1742bff02e44c2ea25649cb45df5103/Pet%20Application%20Form%20December%202020.pdf
If the dog you're interested in seems compatible with your lifestyle we'll set up a time for you to meet the dog privately.
PLEASE NOTE: Indigo Rescue only adopts to homes within 30 miles of Beaverton because our volunteers deliver all of our dogs to their adoptive homes. We work very hard to create a family of our Indigo Rescue adopters because we want to be close enough to help in case there are any problems. We want everyone to be happy and successful!

**ALL of our dogs and puppies come vaccined to their age, spayed/neutered and microchipped.

Thank you for your interest in adopting and saving a life.

animal.description: Harley is an adorable little 9 week old girl who came up from New Mexico with her sister Charlie. A bit timid at first, she quickly warmed up and now wants nothing more than to be close to "her people." Harley is not a clingy puppy, but does prefer to be in close proximity to her humans. She's content to nap at your feet or on a nearby dog bed, or just sit and watch the activity in her busy foster household. She's a confident pup, but also cautious when approaching something new. She mastered stairs and the doggy door very quickly, will sit for treats, and is working hard on potty training. Harley is in a foster family with 4 year old and 8 year old children and is not fazed by their rambunctious play. She fit right in with the two resident adult dogs and is happy to romp and roughhouse with them in the yard. Harley will be a medium to large size dog when full grown, so will definitely need a yard or lots of outdoor exercise to burn off energy. And that soft downy coat that makes her so cuddly will also need regular brushing. Harley is being fostered in Arvada and will be ready for adoption after January 29th.

This is sweet Snowball.  He is a 2 year old wired hair Jack Russell Terrier mix who is all of 11 pounds. He was brought in Christmas Eve by his owner as he was going to Boot Camp and could no longer care for him.  Snowball was pretty fearful at first - which is to be expected as his whole life was turned upside down.  It took some time and patience and of course lots of love but we soon gained his trust and now he is the happy go lucky boy we knew he could be!  He seems more at ease with women then men but certainly lets our male staff members hold and take care of him.  He LOVES other pups, and his perfect home would have another pup that could show him the ropes as he may find a new environment again pretty scary.

He has been a joy to have with us but he is ready to go to his forever family- we're confident he will make his adopters a terrific companion. Please copy and paste the link below (or above) into your browser to fill out our online application. Please hurry so you don't miss out as we expect good response. Snowball is up to date on all shots and dewormings and carries an adoption fee of $399 which includes his micro chip.  Don't delay, get your application in to his coordinator at

animal.description:
This little Merle Chihuahua is amazing. The rescue was contacted about a blind Chihuahua in need to be rehomed. Who can say no to that??
wonder arrived and of course, she was confused and disoriented. She immediately attached to her human and hasn't left.
As the weeks have gone by, she has blossomed and navigates with no issues. She is totally house broke and has never had an accident. Since she did not really respond well to her name we dubbed her Stevie Wonder and call her Stevie. 
Having a vision-impaired dog takes a special person. Although Stevie is very low maintenance, she needs to always be kept safe. She needs a very secure yard, probably no steps, and a person who does not mind a bed partner. Once acclimated into a new home, Stevie is confident, assured and just a "Wonder" to watch.
She comes when called, is a great foot warmer and is very charming. 
After being in her foster home a week or so, her foster mom panicked when she could not find her. Turns out, Stevie is very found of the couch and fuzzy blankets.
Stevie will be spayed soon, vaccinated, and microchipped. 
She will be available to go to her new home mid February.
We do not do out of Oklahoma adoptions and we do not transport dogs out of state.
If you are interested in Stevie, please email the reuse for an application to be sent.
Her adoption fee is $225.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Staffie Mix| 10 mos|55 lbs.|$450.000Hello friends! I'm Blue Moon! Since COVID took away happy hours, let me bring the happy hour TO YOU! Every hour is a happy hour with me by your side!
I'm a very handsome 10 month old American Staffordshire boy looking for an amazing home to call me own! I'm a big goof ball, like one would expect of my breed. I like to play play play! If there's another dog to wrestle, I'm game! I am super respectful with other dog's wishes. There's a couple little dogs at my foster home that are elders, and if the tell me to back off and mind my biz, I do that. After all, I'm the new guy here and I don't mean to start any trouble. Not sure if I've met any cats, but I would likely respect them as well. I'm still a pup and learning the ropes on how to be a great ambassador for my breed! The perfect home would be one that can work with me on basic training and socializing like every young pup needs. I already know how to sit so that's a great start! I am motivated by treats and I want to please my people! I am a STRONG bully boy, and i am still learning how to walk on a leash without pulling. Hopefully we can go for walks and you can leach me these skills! I'm quiet in a crate for bedtime and doing well with house training in my foster home. There are little kids at my foster home and I've been good with them also. They like to have fun, just like me!
If you're looking for a hippopotamus to be your new best friend, I'm your boy! I promise to keep you laughing and loved for years to come! Pick me! Pick me!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Fill out an Adoption Application
Titus 2 year old Great Dane . He is a calm, laid back guy. He can be a little shy at first, but very quickly warms up with a few head pets and butt scratches.
He is very smart, listens well and a total cuddle bug!
He does have a bite history with a child, therefore he should go to a home with no kids.
Likes: affection, relaxing, squeaky toys
Dislikes: rain, doorbells
Personality: he is incredibly sweet, people pleaser, playful at times
Temperament: easy going, calm, gentle
Energy level: low - gets a small spark of energy a couple times a day, but mostly lounges around
Favorite activities: sleep, watching birds, squeaking his toy
Good with cats/dogs: chases cats, good with dogs
Housetrained: yes
Crate trained: yes
Challenges: none so far
Medical issues: none
Best type of home: calm, quiet home with adults and/or low energy dogs. No kids or cats.
Titus is being fostered in Glouster, VA!Application Fees, Adoption Donations and Rescue Policy: Please know that 100% of our funds are used for rescuing the dogs.
Our rescue policy requires the following:

Adopters must have their primary residence in one of the following states: Pennsylvania, Ohio, New Jersey, Delaware, Maryland, West Virginia, Virginia, and parts of North Carolina and parts of New York.
We will not adopt a giant breed dog to homes where the dog will have access to highly varnished hardwood steps inside the home. Any inside steps to which the dog(s) have access, must have carpeting, securely fixed stair treads, or a non-skid surface. We encourage you to remediate potential safety issues while your application is under review, prior to the home visit.
Methods or devices using pain or force on the dog to control the dog, or to deter undesirable behavior is prohibited.
Applications for giant breed dogs must be submitted by the property owner.
Homes with children under 6 years of age will not be approved for adoption.
Homes with children should have a fenced yard.
Pets currently in the applicant's home must have a history of appropriate veterinary care. Veterinary records will be checked.
All references must be checked before any visitation of the dog is permitted at the foster home.
All family members must be present during the home visit to the applicant's home.
Any dog(s) in the applicant's home must have an introductory meeting with the rescue dog being considered, before any adoption can be completed.
Homes with intact dogs will not be approved for adoption. Exceptions to this policy can be found on the Adoptable Dog Page.

For additional information please review our FAQs or contact mastiffstomutts@gmail.com
Mastiffs To Mutts Rescue reserves the right to approve or deny any adoption that occurs through this organization without disclosure. We reserve the right to make exceptions for special circumstances.

animal.description:
Please only send inquires to the email in this bio all others will not be answered. Please read the bio before sending questions - we answer all we know about the dog here.

Meet Georgia who arrived to Florida from rural Georgia where she was living under an abandoned trailer with her 10 puppies, all of which have been placed in their forever homes! Now it is Miss Georgia's turn!!

At an estimated age of only 2 years old; she is currently receiving treatment for heart worms and her X-rays showed bullets in her body. She is up to date on vaccinations and will be scheduled to be spayed and microchipped.

Through a life of anything but ease, this sweet girl is still trusting, no grumbles or grunts being carried as she learned to go in out of the house on her own, a very new experience for her. She is still timid, but that tail remains wagging constantly and she willingly follows a gentle toned voice.

She has quickly grasped house training, no accidents, and enjoys spending time in her chair, her absolute happy place. Her temperament is so calm, she loves being loved on but also appreciates her quiet time.

Georgia deserves a very loving home and a quiet, comfy place to call her own.

If interested in adopting Georgia please fill out the application on the Heidi's Legacy website only.

Georgia's adoption fee is $300 - obedience training is required after adoption.

Obedience training is also required for all our pups. We understand with what is going on in the world that this may be a bit delayed. Please email us the completion certificate.

To apply to foster or adopt please fill out application at

www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

Thank you for completing the application. We are all volunteers and short on time, we will contact you back only if we have more questions or your application is approved and you will be invited to meet the dog. We apologize for not being able to answer everyone back.

For more information contact Kelly.V@HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

DOGS are in Foster Homes. There is NO shelter.

**Our companions MUST live in your home as part of your family.**We do not transport.

**See our website for more information. www.HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

All communication is thru email so please be patient with us. We are all volunteers and work full time jobs and have families of our own.

It takes anywhere between 3-7 days to process an application - the more complete the application the easier it is for us to process it. Please notify your vet that we will be contacting them and to release information to us.

ADOPTION PROCESS:

1. Complete this application
www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

***Everyone must submit an application - we only keep them on file for 1 month

2. Application background check, vet check, etc

3. Invitation thru email to meet the dog(s).

4. Adoption Contract

animal.description:
Sweet Rosemary (Rosie) is an 6-month-old Pit bull mix. Rosie has a lot of puppy energy! She loves to play with her brother and loves to show you how much she loves you by giving you snuggles and kisses! Once she gets wiped out, she loves taking naps. She tries to jump up and make sure you know she's there, but if you come down to her level and give her attention she's pretty good. She does pretty well with other dogs, but hasn't been exposed to too many, so we try to make sure to give a slow introduction so we don't overwhelm or startle her. She's learning to be crate/house trained. Rosie is such a sweet girl and is so patiently waiting for her forever home.

Her adoption fee is $250 which includes age-appropriate vaccines, microchip, and spay. 

To adopt me, please fill out an adoption application on the Lucky 13 Rescue website www.lucky13rescue.org
Or use the link below
https://forms.gle/Tc2jvVQ1oYjPSwmeA

Loves people and giving kisses.
Sleeps in her crate snuggled into her blankets.
Enjoys playing with her foster sister any chance she gets.
Cat friendly
She is working on potty training, most of the time she does good.
Likes to snack on coconut oil, bananas, strawberries & carrots.Thank you for your interest in adopting a pet from Guardians of the Green Mile Inc. We are a group of individuals that have come together to save the lives of animals that are in danger of being euthanized. We raise funds to fully vet the animals and to provide them with a stable home until they are adopted. All of the dogs in our Rescue are in Foster homes while they are looking for their forever family. The only time we put a dog in boarding is for a Foster to go on vacation if another Foster is not able to care for them. We appreciate your taking the time to fill out the application to adopt one of our Guardians of the Green Mile pets. The questions that we ask are to only find the right fit for all of our dogs and the families that will be adopting them. Adoption donation is $300.00 for dogs over 1 year old and $350 with a $50.00 spay / neuter deposit for puppies/dogs under 1 year old.

Click on this link to access the online form, https://www.jotform.us/form/43196636952162

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please click on Snowballs photo to read about her adoption requirements.Snowball was a previous breeder, and after her previous people were finished with her, she was surrendered to a local county shelter. She is enjoying her time in foster care and is learning many skill sets that will help in her forever home. She adores to ride in the car, she is crate trained, and is leash trained too. Now Snowball can just enjoy life- no more puppies! She is an active girl, and needs to be in a home that will continue to provide daily exercise. She would be a wonderful running companion! She enjoys the companionship of other dogs, but prefers dogs that are laid back and smaller than her- oddly enough, she also has an affinity for other female dogs, but the key is their ability to not be too pushy or high-strung. She does require a home without cats.

Snowball has allergies, and has been tested to determine what she is sensitive to. She will need to be maintained on a diet that excludes specific types of food and additives that she is allergic to. Since not all of her allergies are food related, medication will also be needed to alleviate her allergies. Please be sure this is something that you are willing to provide, prior to applying.

Snowball has been spayed, micro-chipped, and is up to date on preventatives. Since she is active, she would do best in a home where all children are 8 years of age or older. She would love a home where her humans are not gone for long hours. A fenced in yard is also a must (structured fencing), she loves to play fetch and explore.

animal.description:
Name:  Tucker
Age: 13
Weight: approx. 15 lbs
Sex/Spayed or neutered?:  Neuter pending
Coat: smooth
Color: black with elegant gray patches
Energy Level: low
Adoption Fee: $100.00
Contact: rescuedogsrgreat@aol.com

Hi everyone! I’m Tucker and I am new to rescue. I used to live with a great family. But when my dad moved he could not have pets in his new home. So, here I am looking for a family to spend my golden years with.

I am a pretty low key guy, but I do have some spunk, especially at chow time and treat time. Foster mom got a video of me so check it out!  I really like to snuggle on the couch with a blanket and I like my doggie bed too. I get along great with my foster brothers and sisters, but am fine being a loner. Saw a cat this morning during my morning walk, and wasn’t interested in her. I have not been around small kids, but given my age, I think a home with older kiddos/no kiddos is more my thing.

Being outdoors is my thing. There is so much to see and do!! I like the yard, but do not try to dig out to see what else it out there. I am really good on a leash and I loves short strolls. I am potty trained and will sit at the back door to let you know when I need to do my business. I can use the doggy door too. Foster mom has put me in a kennel a few times, and I’m cool with that, I just curl up and nap.

I have not seen the doggie doctor for my check-up yet, but that will be soon. Foster mom says I need to be responsible and get neutered—not sure what that is, but I am all about being a good boy!!  My skin is dry and flaking, and my joints are a bit stiff in the morning. And I need to have my teeth cleaned. Foster mom is working on this so I will be ready for my forever home.

I will keep ya’ll posted! If you want more information, email my foster mom!

If you want to help with this dog’s medical expenses: 
https://therescuedrescuers.org/how-to-help

If you want to adopt this dog, apply at the link! 
https://therescuedrescuers.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Watch out world up for debut are the Hamilton County Parks Litter 
These 10 amazing 4-6 pound lab/boxer puppies are 8 weeks old and ready for their furever homes.  They are working on using their puppy pads, they love to play with their stuffed animals (crinkle, squeaky), & love to cuddle and take naps.  They have been fostered with kittens and a young dog. Dad was noted as being a boxer and mom is noted as being a lab.  These babies will melt your hearts. Their adoption fee is $400.00

Richardson Forest Preserve "Richardson", male
he loves puppy cuddles, and playing with his siblings. Richardson's adoption fee is $400

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
Meet Jill ~

My name is Jill and I am a Terrier mix from South Carolina.  I weigh roughly  40lbs.

Along with my brother Jack, we were rescued by a really nice person. She sent us up North so we could find nice families to take care of us and love us.
I am a very nice girl. Not being a barker, pushy or unruly, I am a really easy pup to have around! With my short legs, and chubby body, I am cute as a button!

With my adorable looks, and unbridled loyalty, I will always be there for you through thick and thin. I will never judge you, or turn my back on you. Every single day, you will look at me and you will know that you are loved unconditionally. I will never betray you or hurt you, and I will grow old by your side.

******IMPORTANT - PLEASE READ ALL THE GREAT INFO BELOW******

***Please don't apply unless you are very serious about adopting, and are ready to move forward with the adoption process. We are super busy and make a great effort to respond back to EVERYONE ASAP! WHEN WE TAKE THE TIME TO PROCESS AN APPLICATION AND RESPOND BACK TO THE APPLICANT JUST TO BE EITHER IGNORED OR BE TOLD THEY CANNOT COME FOR SEVERAL DAYS, MORE TIME IS WASTED~PLEASE HAVE MORE RESPECT THAN THAT!

PLEASE read our website's ADOPTION PROCESS PAGE prior to submitting an adoption application. www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-process 
ADOPTION APPLICATION: www.apupspizzazzrescue.com/adoption-application 

ABOUT OUR RESCUE DOGS: 
 All of our dogs are located in Connecticut, are spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccines, microchipped, have been given deworming medications, and have had CT State health checks, & go home with a leash, collar, & packet of medical paperwork. 

BREED IDENTIFICATION:
Please understand that many rescue dogs are mixes of multiple breeds. Petfinder allows us to choose up to two breeds per dog. While the shelters and our rescue do our best in accurately identifying breeds, breed identification is not guaranteed. If there is a certain breed that you do not want, it is very important that you share this with our rescue when applying. When adopting a puppy, breed uncertainty plays a big part in the size/look of the dog as an adult. Please know that any puppy can be a wonderful dog, regardless of preconceived notions of certain breeds, but it is very important that the adopter has the dedication and patience to raise the puppy with boundaries, consistency, structure, & love. The more effort you give towards training & time you allow for exercise, your puppy will grow to be a HUGE source of UNCONDITIONAL LOVE, TOTAL LOYALTY, HAPPINESS, COMFORT & COMPANIONSHIP!

ABOUT OUR RESCUE:
We are a small rescue run by volunteers & focused on finding the right match for both our dogs & for you. If you are interested in adopting through our rescue, you first will need to complete an adoption application & be approved as a potential adopter before meeting any of our pups. No need to be intimidated by our application as it allows us to get to know you & your lifestyle. Of course, the more you can share the better! Please also note, while a fenced yard is fantastic, it is not required by our rescue, however, it may be required for a certain dog occasionally.  Once adoption applicants are approved to become potential adopters, we offer private appointments where you can meet one or several dogs at the discretion of the rescue. We offer a unique & pleasant experience focused on finding the perfect match. It is extremely important to us that everyone is treated with respect & that NO ONE IS LEFT HANGING. WE WILL GET BACK TO YOU WITHIN 2 TO 3 DAYS of application submission. If there is a dog you are eager to meet, please  TEXT US DIRECTLY at 203-241-2351 so that we can check the status of your application and move it forward immediately. We look forward to hearing from you and helping you find your new best friend.

*All adult dogs can be cat tested by request.

HOME/RENTER INSURANCE:
SOME PROVIDERS HAVE VERY STRICT POLICIES REGARDING WHICH TYPE OF DOG BREEDS ARE ALLOWED UNDER THEIR COVERAGE. STATE FARM WAS SUGGESTED TO US AS THEY DO NOT PUNISH, DROP, NOR REFUSE YOU DUE TO DOG BREED SHOULD YOU RUN INTO ISSUES WITH YOUR CURRENT PROVIDER.

animal.description:
Well hello fans!  I’m 2 year old mixed breed Toby from West Virginia, temporarily residing in Westfield, WI. My foster mom calls me a couch potato and I don’t see the point in toys when there is something soft to lay on. I had a traumatic beginning in my life so no matter how sweet you are... I don’t trust you until you prove to me your going to be gentle and kind. I am very chilled in my foster home even with that crazy cat stalking me.  I love massages and enjoy binge watching dog shows on TV.  I am an only dog at the foster home and there are no kiddos so I’m not sure how I would react to those species? I like going outdoors to play in the snow and do my business outside.  I need to be kenneled at night for bedtime or if you go away. I follow my foster mom everywhere when I’m not napping.  I will warm up to you in a few days once I feel settled in and I’ll be your bestie forever.  I just need time to feel safe.  So what do you say?  ?? If you are interested,  my adoption fee is $300 ,  I'm currently not neutered so there will be a $100 refundable fee which will be returned once neutered . You can apply for me at: www.lastpawrescue.org

he loves puppy cuddles, and playing with his siblings. Glen's adoption fee is $400

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.MEET CLYDE! Clyde is a 1-2 year old Pyr mix and weighs 75 lbs. This big guy has come a very long way; he came into rescue very fearful and starving. He has blossomed into a wonderful dog! He is crate trained, leash trained, and treat motivated. He loves goodies and treats of all kinds! He has put weight on and his coat is doing much better! Clyde works with a trainer every week and has learned sit, stay, come, and is working on down. He is learning how to socialize with other dogs, and he plays with a female husky and with a female red heeler. He needs a yard and lots of exercise and someone experienced with his breed. Clyde loves water and loves the pool, even in the winter! Clyde would love a dog playmate in his new home. He is a wonderful big guy and cannot wait loving forever home! Clyde is currently in Texas but can be on the next NW transport.

All our dogs require secure VISIBLE fencing. All current pets in adoptive home must be spayed/neutered and up to date on vaccinations.

Adoption Fee: $350

All of our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations.

Transport Fee: $300

Transport fee includes the cost of transport plus the Health Certificate required for USDA approved transport.

Adoption applications can be found on our website: www.greatpyrsandpaws.org

https://greatpyrsandpaws.rescuegroups.org/forms/form?formid=5959

Northwest adopter pays cost of transport to independent transport company. Transport is arranged by GPPR.

animal.description:
Mille was rescued with 4 other JRT puppies. Millie is not with her littermates, as she has a special purpose. She is helping another puppy we have named Eli. Eli came to us malnourished. His recovery took 6 weeks. He was only 7 weeks old when he came to us. When he recovered he needed a playmate. He needed a puppy his size to show him how to play. You see... Eli is a lab mix. He should be around 15 pounds for his age, but he is only 5 lbs because his growth was stunted. So Millie has become friends with Eli and taught him how to play and interact. They are great buddies.

Now getting back to Millie- This is her story. Mom is a 12-pound JRT and dad is 15 pounds. She is called a Shorty Jack because she has short legs and longer body. She was also born with no tail. She has had her first vaccines, been dewormed, and microchipped. Millie will be spayed on 2/12. She can go for adoption after that, however........unlike her littermates.........she can not go for adoption until Eli is adopted. He needs her. So you can put in an application for her, but we don't know how soon she can leave. 

We require a fenced in back yard (physical fence) and our policy is no small children under the age of 7. Puppies needs a home where a primary adult caretaker is home during the day. If you have other dogs, another small dog 15 pounds and under in the home is acceptable, however no large dogs. 

Adoption fee is $425. Please put in an application on our website www.indianasaveadog.com A $50 deposit (once your application is approved) will hold your puppy until adoption day.

animal.description:
Eli is a very special puppy. He almost died when he was 7 weeks old. He came to us malnourished and he was only 14 ounces. Now he is 13 weeks old and he is a healthy, beautiful and strong boy. He is a lab/ cattle dog mix. At his age now of 13 weeks, he should be over 15 lbs. However, he is only 5 lbs. His growth was stunted. We do not expect him to be over 30 lbs. as an adult.

Eli was bottle fed when he first arrived here. He finally started gaining weight and now he is ready for adoption. Because he was not with any littermates, he did not know how to play with other puppies. Therefore, when we rescued our Jack Russell Terrier litter, we put a JRT, Millie in with him. Millie is a hoot and she shows him how to play and be a puppy. Eli still loves to be held and cuddled. He loves people. He was always held when he first came here. He will sit in your lap quietly and fall asleep. He will gently give you kisses. He loves people.

Eli is growing, and his bones are strong. He will be going for adoption without being neutered. Whomever adopts him will sign a neuter contract and have him neutered around 6-7 months of age or timeframe recommended by the vet. We want his bones to continue to develop and strengthen, and neutering early can deter bone density in male dogs.

He has started his series of puppy shots and is microchipped. We require a fenced in back yard ( physical fence) and please no small children under the age of 10. Eli needs a home where a primary adult caretaker is home during the day. If you have another dog in the home it must be a smaller breed that is friendly. Adoption fee is $300 and we will refund $75 of the adoption fee when proof of neuter is provided. Please put in an application on our website www.indianasaveadog.com

animal.description:
BUSTER is 9 years old and weighs 70 pounds.

HEY,
I am Buster boy and I am just an old softie who loves nothing better than to burrow myself under the covers and snuggle the night away. I had to leave my last house in a big hurry due to some pretty awful stuff happening that I can no longer think about. 

Right now, I'm am putting everything behind me and starting fresh. I am a healthy, happy guy and can follow commands just fine. I know SIT, STAY, SHAKE and LAY DOWN. I do fine in a crate, but even better in a bed - hahahahaha. Right now I get to go into my human's son's bed and boy is it comfortable. I like little humans - mine is about 9 years old I think I heard him say, and we get along just fine. I don't have a lot of experience around smaller ones and CATS - forget it. They are just plain weird. I do like my own kind however. Us dogs rock and roll,

Oh, oh, oh, forgot to tell you that I love walks. We can walk all day as far as I'm concerned. Lots of great smells and adventures to be had out in the woods or the neighborhood.

Do you think you could find a place for me in your heart? I know I have plenty of room in mine for you. 





SIT STAY SHAKE LAYDOWN

NOTE: All of our dogs live in foster homes so it is not possible to setup a meet and greet prior to submitting an adoption application. Filling out an application doesn't obligate you to adopt, but it does save your place in line if there are multiple people interested.

Learn more about the ADOPTION PROCESS here (Type or cut & paste the below website address into your browser): http://www.sdroregon.com/adoption-process.htm

animal.description:
This is Kevin. He’s a big, sweet 9-month old shepherd mix. He’s also quite derpy and playful. Kevin’s former life was in a backyard pen without much socialization other than with his brother (Joe, also with a Lucky13 foster family). Kevin loves other dogs and is great with kids (cats unknown). He prefers not being alone and will follow other dogs around until they either play with him or tell him to go away. He’s discovering that people pats are great, and he will ask for attention with small licks to your hands. Since Kevin had little socialization previously, most things are new to him. Because of this, he can be timid with new people and stands back in new situations until he sees that he’s welcome and safe. He is acclimating well and happily learning the joys of treats and toys and cuddles. He’s also learning all about leashes and while not particularly happy about being alone in a kennel, is managing it as well as can be expected. Kevin is not a jumper and is not showing aggressive behaviors. He’s a big boy who doesn’t realize his size, but still plays He will be a great addition to your family if you give him a chance!

Kevin will come with age appropriate shots, microchip, deworming, and neuter. His adoption fee is $250.

In order to adopt, please submit an application by visiting this page 
https://forms.gle/Tc2jvVQ1oYjPSwmeA 

Lucky 13 Rescue www.lucky13rescue.org

animal.description:
This soulful face belongs to our buddy Baker. Baker is an interesting combination of Party Guy and Shy Guy. While he loves to play and cuddle and go for walks, Baker is also quite unsure of new things and situations. He needs a home that has the time to calmly introduce him to all things that have not crossed his path before. Baker is not a dog for a first time dog owner. Rather we are looking for guardians who are experienced with active large breed dogs. Baker is very strong and with his enthusiasm to play can be a handful. Still he is also cuddly and affectionate and a kind look goes a long way with him. At only 14 months, Baker can be like a very large puppy on the loose. Obedience training is highly recommended for him to become the great adult dog we know he can be. In his last home his energy level was just too overwhelming for their other dog so it would be best if he was an only pup. No cats please. As with all bully breeds, Baker is a sensitive fellow who would love to be someone's couch buddy. Buddy does have allergies to poultry so his diet must be monitored, otherwise he is in great shape. If you are looking for a companion who can fit in for both play and quiet times, Baker may be for you.
Please note, due to the current COVID-19 pandemic our adoption process has changed. 
Please visit our website https://spca.bc.ca/adoption/how-to-adopt/ 
for more information and to apply for the animal you are interested in. All adoptions are by appointment only once we have received and approved an application.

*Due to the high number of applications we receive for our animals, we will only be contacting potential adopters to further review their application. Primary Color: White Secondary Color: Tan Weight: 31.3kg Age: 1yrs 2mths 0wks Animal has been Neutered

animal.description:
This amazing jokester is the full package—athletic, smart, spry, fun-loving, obedient and young enough to take on the world right by your side!  

Please meet Collins!  He is a American Staffordshire Terrier weighing in at 70 lbs of total beauty!  He and his brother, Pilsner, were both strays in Bartlett, Tennessee. Their owners were found, but because he was hit by a car, they chose not to claim either boy. He is doing great now that his elbow dislocation has been repaired. We realize how incredibly difficult it will be to find a home for both of these brothers together, but we are hoping we are due a miracle or two. They both love attention, cuddling on the couch and patrolling the yard. They love playing outside and are learning a few manners along the way. They love to go for rides in the car and truly love each other. They have excellent leash manners, even though they get excited from time to time. They are housebroken and crate trained, but much prefer being out with you. They ABSOLUTELY ADORE TOYS, especially those that squeak and crinkle. You will most likely find them in a toy box, if given the chance.  They have adorable personalities, especially once they get to know you and settle in. They would love going on hikes, spending the day at the beach or sitting by a bonfire. Whatever the adventure, these two are your boys!

If you are interested in these adorable, loving, adventurous young men, please get your apps in as fast as you can!

THE APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PICTURE. 


ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Collins
Breed:  American Staffordshire Terrier
Gender:  Male         
Age:  1 1/2 years      
Weight: 70 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes    
Vaccines: Current                      
Heartworm:  Tested negative on 1/5/2021, currently on Heartgard
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with dogs of various sizes, breeds and genders
Cats:  Unknown
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, older children. He has NOT been tested with infants or toddlers, so proper supervision and introductions would be required. 

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our animals are fostered in various locations in the a South and in New England. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers who work full-time jobs and have animals of our own, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

Please read all about Toby (below) and if you feel you are a good match for him and want to meet him, please complete an application found on our website, Toby’s foster home is in Olympia, WA.
www.mywayhomedogrescue.org

Little Toby was adopted from a shelter in 2019 and his person has recently ended up in the hospital and is now unable to care for him. 

Toby is such a good boy! He is crate trained and does great on leash. He is house-trained, great in the car and good with other dogs. He is a confident dog but not overly bossy. He is an independent boy that will snuggle in his crate (door open) for the night and in the morning awake ready to go.

Toby’s perfect home will have a person or couple that likes walks, car rides and wants a charming, gentle buddy to share their lives. Toby can be an only dog or have a dog buddy in the house hold. Toby has a cat in his foster home and sometimes growls at her but has no issues with her being near him. He has not been tested with children so children over 10 only.

Toby has had his vaccinations, was heart wormed tested, has been neutered, de-wormed, had flea treatment, and is microchipped. His adoption fee is $300 (our senior adoption fee).

animal.description:
This amazing jokester is the full package—athletic, smart, spry, fun-loving, obedient and young enough to take on the world right by your side!  

Please meet Pilsner!  He is a American Staffordshire Terrier weighing in at 70 lbs of total beauty!  He and his brother were both strays in Bartlett, Tennessee. Their owners were found, but because his brother, Collins, was hit by a car, they chose not to claim either boy. We realize how incredibly difficult it will be to find a home for both of these brothers together, but we are hoping we are due a miracle or two. They both love attention, cuddling on the couch and patrolling the yard. They love playing outside and are learning a few manners along the way. They love to go for rides in the car and truly love each other. They have excellent leash manners, even though they get excited from time to time. They are housebroken and crate trained, but much prefer being out with you. They ABSOLUTELY ADORE TOYS, especially those that squeak and crinkle. You will most likely find them in a toy box, if given the chance.  They have adorable personalities, especially once they get to know you and settle in. They would love going on hikes, spending the day at the beach or sitting by a bonfire. Whatever the adventure, these two are your boys!

If you are interested in these adorable, loving, adventurous young men, please get your apps in as fast as you can!

THE APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PICTURE. 


ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Pilsner
Breed:  American Staffordshire Terrier
Gender:  Male         
Age:  2 years      
Weight: 70 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes    
Vaccines: Current                      
Heartworm:  Tested negative on 1/5/2021, currently on Heartgard
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with dogs of various sizes, breeds and genders
Cats:  Unknown
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, older children. He has NOT been tested with infants or toddlers, so proper supervision and introductions would be required. 

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our animals are fostered in various locations in the a South and in New England. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers who work full-time jobs and have animals of our own, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description:
Tina Marina has been described as an “ENGAGING” little dog.  Everyone that meets her falls under her magical spell.  At 10 years old and 4 ½ lbs, she packs an enormous amount of love and loyalty in such a small package.
 
Tina’s background is unknown, but this is what we do know:  
     She acts like a much younger dog.  She will follow you everywhere and melts your heart when she looks at you. 
     She will dance with you.  Yes, she dances.  You can request the video if you want to see it. 
     She is friendly with all people, dogs, cats, and chickens. 
     She is very diligent if she wants something and you will be entertained watching her think and plot how to get it. 
     She is house and crate trained (as long as she can go outside regularly).  She knows how to scratch the door to come in and she even scratched the door once to go out. 
     She is also a great traveler.  She really enjoys a good road trip and is well mannered when visiting other places.
     She has the most adorable growly bark, especially at mealtime.  She will talk to you if you talk to her.
     Tina is fixed and has no teeth.  She has all her immunizations and a clean bill of health from the vet.
 
Please complete an application on our website at http://rescueachi.com/adoption-application/ if you would like to meet Tina Marina, but hurry because she won’t last long!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Did I catch your eye? Learn more about me by reading my profile below; I just might be your new best friend! Apply on our website
(

https://www.healingheartsrescue.org/adopt

)

to

set up a private meeting or check below for my adoption event schedule.

Age: 1 year old

Weight: 45 pounds

Dog friendly: Yes - another dog is REQUIRED in her home

Cat friendly: Unknown

Kid friendly: YES - but prefers a quite home

Potty trained: YES

Crate trained: TBD

FENCED YARD REQUIRED

Do you enjoy relaxing inside, watching your shows, and having a quiet household? Addie does too! She would much rather lay on the couch than go for a walk! Loud noises (and some "not as loud noises" like the printer or blender) are scary and people coming over make her nervous. It takes a bit for her to be comfortable with new surroundings, but when she is-she finds her favorite spots and snuggles right into them. She loves other dogs and gets along with all kinds. She gets along with all humans. Addie comes from an initial situation where she may not have been given space to play or explore. Her previous foster in Texas said she was nervous and shy at first too, but opened up and became super loving, affectionate, and very playful.

She is spayed and potty trained. She hasn't shown confidence in leashes and shys away from going outdoors unnecessarily. The previous foster said she was crate trained, but she hasn't shown interest in going in the one available here. She hasn't met any cats yet, but I think she would be fine with them.

Addie needs someone who will be patient, kind and understanding of her anxiety. She is quiet, smart, sweet and submissive. When she wags her tail you know you've found a way into her heart and it is so rewarding.

Adoption Fee: $425

INTERESTED IN MEETING ME?

If you'd like to arrange a private meeting or begin the adoption process, please fill out an adoption application by visiting

https://www.healingheartsrescue.org/adopt

**Note on breed and age determination:

Breed and age are often determined on appearance, our own knowledge, veterinarian advice, and/or information from the sending shelters or previous owners. Most of our adoptable dogs were previously stray dogs with little history, we can't be 100% sure of a dog's breed mix, and unless there is a specific date of birth listed, we can't be 100% sure of a dog's age. Additionally, our assessments of a dog's interactions with other dogs, cats, or children are based on OUR experiences. Your experience may differ.

ADOPTION FEE INCLUDES:

Wellness check

Spay/neuter (puppies adopted with required spay/neuter certificate)

Age appropriate vaccines - rabies as required by law and distemper combo or proof of positive titer test

Heartworm test if over 7 months of age

Fecal test and/or deworming for parasites

Microchip



~ Healing Hearts rescue will also provide dental procedures, bloodwork, surgeries, and/or any other additional vet work as needed while dogs are in our care.

~ Adoption fees are non-negotiable and fees are listed on the dog's profile

~ Adoption fees can be paid the following ways with the required sales tax (7.525%) added:

PayPal

Credit Card

Cash

WANT TO HELP SAVE MORE DOGS?

Healing Hearts Rescue is a nonprofit, foster-based rescue

located in the Twin Cities area of Minnesota

that is 100% funded through adoption fees and donations

. We are excited for you to join us on this mission to save the lives of dogs in need.

We believe every dog deserves to be loved as true members of a family and are committed to fulfilling that dream one dog at a time! Sign up to foster, volunteer or donate on our
website

Healing Hearts rescue will also provide dental procedures, bloodwork, surgeries, and/or any other additional vet work as needed while dogs are in our care.

animal.description:
Date of birth:  6/24/2019

1/31/2021:  Morris is a super cute American Staffordshire!  He’s a year old and weighs 64 lbs currently.  Morris LOVES people and loves attention! He’s sweet natured and very affectionate. He'd love to just hang out and watch tv with his new person!

• Morris’s left rear leg had been broken awhile back and healed poorly. The head of the femur was shattered. He had FHO surgery to repair it on December 12.  He’s doing pretty well, but not putting enough weight on that leg. We’re doing exercises with him twice a day.  We’ll reevaluate his leg in a couple of weeks and be able to tell you more then.

• Morris is looking for a home with someone who is home quite a lot. He’d been abandoned at his prior home and, understandably, his top priority now is to be with people and not be left alone.  Someone who works from home would be perfect for him.

• Morris needs a home where he'd be an only pet, without other dogs or cats in the home. 

• He’d do best with a house and a wooden privacy fence— he runs the chain link fence when another dog is the adjacent yard. He doesn’t like to be outside alone for long— he wants back inside where the people are.

• He loves food and treats!  He should be easy to train. He takes treats gently.

• He walks nicely on a leash.

• He’s had a hard life and will need someone patient to help him adjust to living in a house, work with him on house training, etc.  

• We don’t want to place him in a home with young kids. We think he would do fine with older kids who’ve lived with dogs and are comfortable with dogs and are respectful. 

• We'd place his energy level at medium.

• He likes to chew Nylabones. He isn’t too interested in toys. He does not chew up bedding or blankets in his kennel. 

• Morris has been neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for heartworms. He’s a real sweetheart and will be a loving and loyal companion.  

MORE ON ADOPTING OUR DOGS... 

> COVID-19 UPDATE:  PLEASE SUBMIT AN ONLINE ADOPTION APPLICATION AND A MEMBER OF OUR ADOPTIONS TEAM WILL REACH OUT TO YOU.  Please visit our web site at HSGKC.ORG for an adoption application, our current COVID-19 adoption protocol, and other adoption info. 

> If you decide you'd like to adopt one of the pets you meet, we reserve the pet for you but we generally don't send the pet home with you that day. We’ll instead schedule a pick up date and time that’s convenient for you.   

> Our goal is to send you home with a healthy pet and any information and support you may need to help your new pet adjust to his or her new home.  All of our dogs & puppies have been spayed or neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, treated for fleas & ticks, tested for heartworms (7 mo. and over), and are on monthly heartworm preventative. Puppies who are too young to receive all the necessary puppy boosters and/or first rabies shot may be brought back to us for those vaccines at no extra charge. You will also receive a leash, collar, coupons for pet supplies and services, toys, and educational materials. And we'll give your dog a bath before he or she goes home! 

> Please note that we prefer and may require a fenced yard for many of our dogs.  Exceptions are made on an individual basis depending on the dog's needs, the person's dog experience, the dog's and person's activity levels, home environment and other factors. 

Thank you for searching for a shelter pet!

Dog Adoption Contact Info:
Email: christine@hsgkc.org
Phone: 913.521.2339
hsgkc.org

animal.description:
Hello Rooney, goodbye heart! This little gent is beyond cute, with his uniquely handsome soft gray coat, adorable markings, and sweet face. Rooney is a quiet guy who loves snacks, cozy beds and his canine and human buddies. Will you be his forever BFF?

* HERE'S WHAT ROONEY'S FOSTER MOM HAS TO SAY! *

Once Rooney warms up to you, he's the sweetest little boy with a lot of pep! Rooney loves adventures and long walks, but is also pretty content to nap the day away with a blanket over his head. He'll paw at you for pets, and will be your tiny shadow! Rooney is great with other people and dogs, and would flourish in a home with lots of attention.

He'll need a new family that has the patience to help him learn to be confident when he's alone and he gets attached to one person, so a home where his 'person' is home a lot would be best for him.

Sandy is an approximate 10 month old lovable girl who loves to play! She is in a foster home with other dogs, cats, and children. She loves to play outside and take a nap in her bed when done, plays well with dogs, and is still learning about the cats. Sandy is very well disciplined, taking direction very well, and learning basic commands. When she needs to go to the bathroom, she lets you know it's time to go outside and is crate trained. 

Sandy's appointment for her spay and microchip is scheduled, on monthly preventions, and she is vaccinated to age. If you are interested in Sandy, email or call us at the contact information provided below.

The Humane Society of Statesboro and Bulloch County is a non-profit animal welfare organization dedicated to Animal Rescue and Low Cost Spay and Neuter Programs. We are a foster care only organization. All of the rescue animals in our care are living in foster home environments.
If you are interested in meeting one of our 'Foster Fur Kids' call us at 912-681-9393 or email us at @ borohumane@gmail.com.
Adoption Applications are available at statesborohumane.org.
Stop by one of our adoption events, fundraisers or our Thrift Store (ReTails) to get involved. 
TOGETHER WE CAN SAVE LIVES!

animal.description:
Watch out world up for debut are the Hamilton County Parks Litter 
These 10 amazing 4-6 pound lab/boxer puppies are 8 weeks old and ready for their furever homes.  They are working on using their puppy pads, they love to play with their stuffed animals (crinkle, squeaky), & love to cuddle and take naps.  They have been fostered with kittens and a young dog. Dad was noted as being a boxer and mom is noted as being a lab.  These babies will melt your hearts. 

Miami Whitewater "Miami" or Mimi", female
diva-she is one of the smaller puppies and has figured out a way to squeeze through the puppy pen bars, she loves attention, she follows her foster moms around and howls if she does not get the attention that she wants, she loves to snuggle in the cat bed, she loves to be cuddled. Miami's adoption fee is $400

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
My name is Maisie is and I'm a sweet, fun and energetic 11-week-old Husky mix puppy.

I am deaf but have learned how to sit for food. I am definitely a little stubborn and learning how to follow commands - but it's difficult.. Once I "get it",  I just want to lay and curl up in your arms.

I love to play with other dogs but sometimes I get a little hyper and nippy. I also play a little too rough sometimes with cats especially with ones that don't want to be near me. Please don't walk up from behind me and surprise me ever - but especially when I'm eating!  I love my chow and can get a bit reactive/aggressive if that happens!

Because of my special needs, I won't be adopted out to an environment with children under 10 years old.

It will take someone who has a lot of time to devote to training a deaf dog and a lot of one-on-one attention to be my perfect match.

I am up to date with age appropriate vaccinations and have been dewormed.  I'm not yet spayed as I am too small and young.  My adoption fee is $350 with $100 to be returned to my adopter once they have me spayed. 

To request an adoption application, please visit https://www.udranch.org/contact.  Please allow 24-48 hours for a response!
