animal.description:
Cali ACCT-A-83487 

Intake: Owner Surrender (Fighting with other Dog in the Home)
Age: 4Y
Sex: Female
Altered: Yes

**I'd prefer a home without other dogs. I want to be your one and only!**
**This dog would do best in an adult only home. **

Medical Observation:
1/31 (Vet Check)-- Previously spayed female, tattoo and spay scar observed. Multiple puncture wounds to left side of face around ear, lower jaw and side of face. All wounds are already scabbing over, no pocketing. Wounds do not need to be surgically repaired, should all respond well to medical management. 
1/30 (Vet Check)-- The patient has a bite wound from earlier today that appears relatively mild. She will be treated with pain medication and antibiotics while awaiting anesthetized wound care tomorrow.
1/30 (Triage Exam)-- dog is BAR and not really interested in food at time of exam, she was bleeding from her mouth and had some dried blood in her left ear. she also had cut and puncture wounds all over her face

Behavior Observation: 
1/30 (Per Vet)-- Nervous, but friendly. Very head shy - examination of wounds limited 
1/30 (Per Previous Owner)--she is very nice. she loves to run, she should not be around other dogs. Knows commands like sit, lay down, go to bed, go potty. she does not like hoodies. She is great on the leash.

BITE DETAIL--
1/30/21- The owners other dog and Cali were outside in the yard with the owners wife while she was cleaning. The other dog was sniffing a feather on the ground and Cali charged at her and bit her chest and Cali also bit the other dog nose. There were no triggers like food, Cali just attacked. Nothing in her body language alerted either owner to the attack coming. Cali has bitten the other dog before. The first incident was over food. A potato chip fell on the floor and both the dogs went after the chip at the same time. The other dog does not have to do anything to provoke Cali, it can be as simple as walking past her and Cali will lunge for her.

Intake:Owner Surrender

Dodges leash initially but able to be leashed with a wide loop when treats are dropped on floor. Pulls strongly on leash darting in front of handler. Outside, urinates and defecates and then starts pulling immediately back to the door. Did not attempt handling due to nervousness. Jumps right back into kennel and tries to retreat to back of kennel with leash on. Handler lets leash go so as to not hold her back and then coaxes her back to the front with treats. Drops treats on floor and able to loosen leash and drop it to floor before removing it from kennel. After closing kennel door, Hemi stays at front of kennel and licks hand through the bars.
1/31 (Per Owner) Mild mannered, Does not get along with other dogs, Lived with childred

animal.description:
**Please read Brownie's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

Meet Brownie, a 3-year old, 33-pound, Mountain Cur/Dachshund/Beagle mix fellow.

Brownie is a happy, generally outgoing, though sometimes shy, sweet boy. He is kind and gentle and would make a great dog for a family with children, but he is laid back enough to companion an older person just as well.

He’s a loving, affectionate dog, who loves to play with other dogs, but is especially responsive to human attention. 

Don’t those eyes just melt your heart?!

All dogs are up to /date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  All dogs require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Brownie, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $495]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

#711654Age: 5 years. Weight: 56 lbs How this pet arrived: This pet was brought in by their Previous Owner on January 31, 2020. At SDHS:This pet has been vaccinated, microchipped and neutered. This pet is now ready for their new home! Why this pet is the one for you:Abram is intelligent and driven by the need for speed! Huskies were bred to run while pulling something heavy for miles in polar conditions so giving them enough exercise is no easy feat! The average dog may be happy with 2-3 30 min walks daily , but that won't cut it for this guy! Abram craves adventure and if you don't give him what he needs he'll go look for it on his own! Huskies are escape artist who could give Houdini a run for his money. They can jump over, dig under, or swim around any obstacle between them and a good time. For that reason, having a yard isn't what is important for a dog like Abram. He is a marathon mutt who is looking for an athletic human who has the same compulsion to wake up and GO every single day. If you love to run, bike, Rollerblade, skateboard, or hike, and you are looking for a dog with endurance and energy then Abram may be your guy! If your daily work outs have become stale and you're looking for a partner to bring new excitement to your runs, bikes, or hikes then what are you waiting for? Make an appointment to learn more about this wild man today!

animal.description:
Boxy headed, big hearted goofball loversJarvis is waiting for you. And by waiting, we actually mean he is running around the farm, having a blast, making buddies at every turn, eating like a champ and overall winning over everyone he meets to the Boxy Head Lovers Club at Saving Grace. Jarvis is a young lab mix who is about a year or so old and weighs around 40 lbs now but needs to gain a few as he isn't as bulky as he should be. No worries, he is working daily on that btw. Jarvis would easily melt into a home with other dogs as he seems always on the lookout for partners in crime, and by crime, we mean being ridiculously cute exploring and doing zoomies. Jarvis may not have a lot of home training yet, but he is a gentleman and waits in his crate for meals as well as his time out. He would make a fab adventure buddy as he would likely be up for anything from trips to Lowes, where he could woo all the ladies, to hikes in the mountains and summers at the beach. He is game for it all! Jarvis would love as many family members as he can find and is ready to become one to your clan.

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Fridays and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

When we were asked to take Annie, we were told that she’s deaf.  After having her with us for a bit, we’d have to agree.  At a minimum, Annie is hearing impaired.  Deaf pups, especially the young ones like Annie at only 12 weeks old, should pick up hand signals quite well.  She’ll be a medium sized lady when she’s all grown up.  Her adoption fee is $225.


All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

animal.description: Roscoe is a 35 lb good natured, happy 3.5 year old Pug/Beagle.  A typical Beagle, he knows & responds to his basic commands most of the time - sit, stay, lie down, come -- but is curious, smart, & can be distracted by more interesting things. He loves long daily walks- the earlier in the day the better, 2 x per day even better!  It helps to keep him settled. He loves his long walks along the Humber with his foster Mom!  He enjoys playtime & snuggling in his very calm, quiet foster home where he follows Mom around. "Music for my dog" on YouTube works for him!  He's friendly & great with people & other low key friendly dogs. He loves cats a little too much for their comfort & gets in their face. Roscoe was rescued from an intolerable situation, where he was passed around from home to home. He is highly anxious & fearful of loud noises, yelling, screaming, & banging. He then chases his tail & runs to find a 'safe' place.  He's much more settled now. We are looking for a quiet, adult experienced home with a low activity level where he can continue to progress. A home close to parks & trails, with a fenced backyard would be preferred.  Someone who works from home & has time to engage with him would be best. No kids/no grandkids/no noisy neighbourhood/no condos or apartments.  Interested?  Contact Sue:  sgaskell@sympatico.ca.  Adoption fee: $800.
animal.name: Roscoe

animal.description:
Brindy cali is a female, 10 week old 16lbs (will be larger fully grown)
1/4 English bulldog 1/4 Boston terrier and half super mutt mix. We think these pups will be medium to large 45-60#
These are very social and friendly puppies who love people and cats and kids.

Brindy Cali have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Brindy Cali? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Brindy Cali.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Brindy Cali the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!
animal.name: Brindy Cali

animal.description: Woof, woof! I'm so excited you're thinking about adopting a new fur-ever family member! Here are a few things that may help you with your big decision. First, dogs just want to be happy and feel loved. Living inside and being a part of the family is really important to us. A lot of the things you need as humans to stay happy and healthy, us dogs need too. We depend on you for things like vet visits, nutritious food, clean water, social and play time with people and other pets, training classes, toys, and of course, lots of love and attention! Regular baths, nail trims and grooming help us to look and feel our best, while monthly flea and heartworm prevention help us to stay healthy. Did you know that depending on our size and breed, dogs can live up to 20 years? Just think of the wonderful life we could have together!

animal.description: Hello, my name is Duke! I was surrendered to the shelter because I was not getting along with the existing dog in my house. I'm a very mouthy young dog. I have an inappropriate playstyle and display some rude behaviors. The behavior team here at the shelter have noticed that I seem to enjoy conflict. This is important information to know because it will affect the methods used for handling and training me to make sure I am successful in my new home. My new home should consist of adults only who have prior dog handling experience. Continued obedience training and keeping me mentally/physically fullfilled will be a must. Please keep checking my profile for updates as the staff gets to know me better! If this dog has been successful in our play groups it is not a guarantee that a dog will be social with other dogs in their home or in public settings. Dogs are individuals and have personality conflicts, just like us. Play groups do not guarantee that territorial or resource guarding issues will not surface in the home. While play groups do help us get to know the dog's better, once they are adopted their new environments and new relationships will influence their behavior in ways we cannot predict. The Adoption Fee Includes: - initial canine distemper combination vaccination - first worming or stool check - rabies vaccination (for animals over 3 months of age) - AVID microchipping - flea treatment/preventative - spaying or neutering Adoption fee: $135.00 Per state law, ALL ADOPTERS must purchase a non-refundable 2021 dog license at time of adoption for any canine three months and older. The cost of the license is $7.00. (Senior Citizen or Person with Disability-$5.00) Leash and collar included

animal.description:
HI, my name is Jack, I'm just about 2 years old, they call me a "Tennessee mix". I'm what you would call a 40lb lap dog. 

I love people, of all ages. My foster home has 3 kids, 4 to 14, and I love to play with all of them. I haven't been around other dogs, but being I’m a pretty submissive male and I think I would like them. 

I enjoy playing with my toys, balls (I'm working on playing catch, I throw the ball to myself sometimes) taking long walks or short, your choice. I am completely housebroken, and semi crate trained. I would enjoy a home where someone is home most of the time, like I said, I love my people. I would like a fenced yard, but it’s not a must as long as you like to take walks.  

I'm a great dog, looking for my own family to love!
Our standard adoption fee is $375 cash or check and $385 credit card ($10 processing fee). .  It includes spay/neuter when age appropriate at our participating vets, age appropriate core vaccinations, fecal testing, deworming, flea and tick preventative,1st vet visit at one of our participating vets, and micro-chipping. 


We must have an application, conduct a phone interview, and meet your entire family to approve an adoption. Please email adopt@safehavendogsIL.org for an application or additional details.

Please note that the breeds and sizes posted in this biography are educated best guesses and are not guaranteed.

Please consider becoming a foster home while you search for your new best friend. We need foster homes - pounds are overflowing with puppies and adult dogs that are at-risk and need help. We can only rescue as many as we have foster home commitments. Fostering is a rewarding experience for your family.

animal.description:
**Please read Boomer 's entire profile, which includes a link to the adoption application. Thank you!** 

This is Boomer, a 2-year old, 45-pound, Mountain Cur/Shepherd mix young fellow.

Handsome Boomer can be shy when he first meets someone, but he’s a very kind and gentle dog who is basically very happy and loving.

Once he gets to know someone, he comes out of his shell and lavishes you with the full shine of his shining, sunny, affectionate personality. He loves children and although he can be a little wary around a new dog, when he gets to know the other pup, he makes fast friend.

Boomer’s only drawback is that he does occasionally get carsick.

All dogs are up to date on vaccinations and spayed/neutered at the time of adoption.  All dogs require professional training to become the best family member they can be.

To adopt or learn more about Boomer, you must fill out an adoption application. To find the application, copy and paste this URL into your browser: WWW.GDRNE.COM/ADOPTION-APPLICATION [Adoption Fee: $495]  **  PLEASE READ: If a dog is listed, then s/he is currently available for adoption. Their information is correct to the best of our abilities and the information we have been given as of the day of posting. Please note, GDRNE does not guarantee the breed of any dog or puppy unless stated that we have run DNA. All breeds listed are educated estimates. Our dogs are rescued from various situations. It is most likely that both their parents were strays and even if not, mixes of some sort and that their grandparents were mixes as well. The dog may have some genetic material of an American Staffordshire Terrier (pit bull). The dogs are usually mixes of many breeds, making them a breed all their own - a True and adorable American MUTT. If you are interested in this dog, you must submit an application. Great Dog is not a shelter so there is no building you can visit. Our dogs live in private foster homes until adopted. To learn more about our *shelterless* rescue, adoption fees, and procedures, review the list of Frequently Asked Questions on our website at WWW.GDRNE.COM.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
PittieLove Rescue, Inc. a 501c3 orgainization is an all-volunteer, foster home based rescue.

Adoption Fee: $450

Our information is current if you are interested please fill out an adoption form here

http://www.pittieloverescue.org/adoption-application

It is the easiest way to start the communication and adoption process.
Meet Zelda! This 7-month old floppy and playful puppy came to us after being found as a stray. Zelda is charmingly puppy-like in all that she does and is always up for adventure. She enjoys being close to her humans - on the couch, in the yard, and as an adorable co-pilot in the front seat on rides. In fact, Zelda is a New Englander at heart and loves frolicking in the snowa snow bunny who also loves toys and chewing on nylabones. And her mischievous side loves stealing things that aren't hers.

Zelda knows basic commands, walks well on leash, and is easy at bath time. She is working on basic manners (like puppy mouthiness and jumping) and is picking up housetraining like a champ. She is an eager beaver when it comes to pleasing her humans and indiscriminately affectionate with those she holds dear.

Zelda is working on her doggie manners when playing with her canine foster brother. She plays rough, so the best canine siblings would be tolerant and able to correct her when they had enough. And she's a little too interested in kitties to live with one. This lanky lady will make someone a terrific friend!www.pittieloverescue.org

Please consider a donation so that we may continue the important work we do.

animal.description:
PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Fridays and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

Indy is a 10 month old beauty who is supposed to be a Boxer/Bully mix.  We honestly don’t know what her breed is but those eyes will steal your heart.  Indy is somewhat apprehensive around the human males and we’re not sure why.  She might do best as  a girl’s girl.  She weighs about 30 pounds and her adoption fee is $175.

All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

Hi my name is Clara. I'm approximately 8 months old. I was found running by the river in Dayton. I am deaf and require a special home. I am super smart and have a lot of potential. I have already learned several hand signals. My favorite things to do are play, eat, sleep and snuggle. I love other dogs, especially dogs closer to my size and I absolutely love people. However I'm not so sure about cats. I will require a lot of patience, understanding and love. Are you the right family for me? I can provide you with a lifetime of love. Clara's adoption fee is $200. She is up to date on age appropriate vaccinations, spayed, and microchipped.
All of our dogs are spayed or neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped and if over 6 months of age, heartworm tested and on heartworm preventative in their foster home.

We require an approved application to meet any of our dogs. We do not have a shelter location and will not arrange a meeting without an approved application.

We strive to make sure the bios provided for our dogs are complete and accurate; we do understand that mistakes happen, however, so if you absolutely cannot find the answer to your question in the dog's bio, you can contact us for more information.

We require a home visit for each dog we adopt out, so we adopt within a 2 hour radius of Dayton, OH. If you are outside of this radius, we encourage you to contact your local rescue or shelter.

animal.description:
LOOKING FOR HER FOREVER HOME.

COURTESY POSTING ONLY - Please go to bigloveanimalrescue.org to apply 


MEET GODIVA! She is a 10-week-old Pitbull mix and weighs about 12lbs! We were originally on a rescue for another dog when our director Lisa spotted Godiva and her brother being transported loosely in the bed of a truck. When Lisa inquired with the drivers, they said the puppies were for sale and Lisa paid them off to bring these babies into our care for medical, and to find them an incredible forever home.


Godiva is super friendly, smart, curious and adventurous. She greets every human and dog with a wagging tail and just as much as she loves to play with her brother and other dogs, she loves for the humans to join. While playful, she is also very laid back and will put herself to bed when she’s tired. According to her fosters, she is nearly potty trained and we’re very happy about that!

Godiva is going to grow up to be a big, strong girl (60-70lbs) and will need a dedicated family preferably with bully breed experience who will give her LOTS of needed daily exercise. Like any of our Pitties, her adopter will be required to invest in training! Applicants must have a backyard and preferably another doggy sibling.


Please apply on our website in order to be considered www.bigloveanimalrescue.org


Applicants must be based in Southern California and if there are children in the home, children must be 10+ years or older.


Adoption fee is $500. Our rescue covers microchip, vaccinations to adoption date and spaying at one of our veterinarians in Los Angeles when she is old enough.


If you're interested in GODIVA, please visit our website and fill out an application here: https://bigloveanimalrescue.org/adoption-application-form/

 

**No meet and greets prior to approved application**

animal.description:
Looking for an all around fun dog?  Gypsy just may be your girl!  Although it took her about an hour or two to warm up, Gypsy is an absolute gem.  Gypsy just loves life and is always happy.  

She loves hopping in your lap and rolling around for belly rubs.  Gypsy is definitely a lover and will give you endless kisses.  Gypsy is great with several of the dogs in her foster home.  As I type she is wagging her tail playing with some of the pups.  She does well in the crate and has not had any accidents. 

Gypsy has had no formal training but is quick to learn.  She has already worked on mastering sit for treats, lol, and we began working on down as well.  Gypsy would love to learn other tricks either through informal or formal training. 

 Gypsy does need a little leash work however that is very typical of rescue pups.  Gypsy would be a great walking companion once she masters these skills but don’t worry, not a walker, she will be just as content hanging out on the couch with you.  

Gypsy is a one year old possible mountain cur/boxer mix that is approximately fifty pounds.  This gal has the softest fur and beautiful markings on her paws and muzzle.  If Gypsy sounds like the perfect dog for you, apply today to meet this sweetie.  

If you would like to meet Gypsy, please go to our website at www.rescueahart.org and fill out an online adoption application. 

All HART dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped and up to date on all vaccines, including bordatella and rabies.   They are heartworm tested and on preventative for heartworm, fleas, and ticks.   If you are interested in any of our pets, you must complete an online dog adoption application   at www.rescueAhart.org .   The application will put you in touch with this wonderful dog's foster family so you can schedule a meeting.   Thanks!   www.rescueAhart.org

animal.description:
Joe cali is a male, 10 week old 16lbs (will be larger fully grown)
1/4 English bulldog 1/4 Boston terrier and half super mutt mix. We think these pups will be medium to large 45-60#
These are very social and friendly puppies who love people and cats and kids.

Joe have your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME.  Want to adopt me?  
Interested in becoming a forever home for Joe Cali? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Joe Cali.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and joe Cali the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!

animal.description:
Are you looking for a gymnast of your very own?  She is the full package—athletic, smart, spry, fun-loving, obedient and young enough to take on the world right by your side!  Shhhh!  Don’t tell her that she is a tripod, she has no idea!

Please meet Sassy Pants!  She is a Lab mix weighing in at 35 lbs of total cuteness!  This sweet young lady was living on the streets, eating chicken bones and dodging cars, when her luck finally ran out!  Unfortunately for her, the vet was unable to save her leg, but fortunately, it has not stopped her zest for life. This adorable girl is also the slickest bag lady this side of the Rio Grande. She can nab something and save it for later, without you even realizing she was up. She doesn’t destroy her finds, but she knows she may need them for later. So....grab a buggy and have it waiting!  She loves attention, cuddling on the couch and chasing a toy or a friend!  She loves playing outside and is learning a few manners along the way. She still likes to help you cook, if you will let her, and she can find every morsel that you drop. She is learning commands, walks very well on a leash and loves to ride in a car. She will try to get out with you, just in case you need help, and riding shotgun is super fun!  She is housebroken and crate trained, but consistency is key to her continued training. She loves to play with friends and take leisurely strolls patrolling the yard. She ABSOLUTELY ADORES TOYS, especially those that squeak and crinkle. You will most likely find her in a toy box, if given the chance.  She loves to snuggle with her friends and sleeping on her back is totally awesome. She has an adorable personality, especially once she gets to know you and settles in. She will need a friend to keep her company and a fenced in yard to run and play. She would love going on short hikes, spending the day at the beach or sitting by a bonfire. Whatever the adventure, she is your girl!  

If you are interested in this adorable, loving, adventurous girl, please get your apps in as fast as you can!

THE APPLICATION LINK CAN BE FOUND ON OUR PETFINDER PAGE UNDER THE PICTURE. 


ANIMAL INFORMATION:  
Name:  Sassy Pants
Breed:  Lab mix
Gender:  Female         
Age:  2 years             
Weight: 35 lbs           
Spayed/Neutered: Yes                
Vaccines: Current                      
Heartworm:  Tested negative, currently in Heartgard
Microchipped: Yes

FOSTER EVALUATION AND RECOMMENDATION:
Dogs:  Yes, fostering with dogs of various sizes, breeds and genders
Cats:  Unknown 
Other Small Animals:  Unknown
Children:  Yes, She has NOT been tested with infants or toddlers, so proper supervision and introductions would be required. 

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
We are a foster-based animal rescue and we thank you for your interest in one of our animals. Our animals are fostered in various locations in the a South and in New England. Our fosters and adoption coordinators are the backbone of what we do. Our fosters work tirelessly to integrate our rescue animals into their home, so that we can provide as much information to potential adopters as possible. In addition, our coordinators offer as much information regarding the medical and behavioral and personality characteristics as is known to our organization. Without them, and our extremely generous donors, we would not be able to save as many animals as we do every day. With each adoption, we operate a Pay It Forward program, whenever possible, to help other animals in our rescue and future animals in need. 

If you are interested in one of our animals, please complete an application. The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture. You may also find our application on our website at www.petmatchmakerrescue.com under the Adopt page. If they are listed on our website, their adoptions have not been finalized yet. That does not mean that we have not received several applications, already. Please complete an application if you are interested and we will keep you apprised of their current status. We are all volunteers who work full-time jobs and have animals of our own, so please be patient with us. We will get back with you as quickly as possible.  

If you are interested in fostering for our organization, please complete an application.  The application link can be found on our Petfinder homepage under the picture.

animal.description:
If you want to save a dog...Thor is your guy! 

Do to the quick actions of one of our volunteers, Thor, and another dog he was with were saved from a lift of over breeding.  He had no vet care and was tied to a chain all day and night.  Thor was just a puppy.  We hate to think of what his life would have been. 

But, don't worry! Thor doesn't care about any of that.  He lives for TODAY and  wants an owner that will give him what he needs love and guidance.  Thor would do great in training and he comes with free lessons to help you bond with him!  He is an active dog and will need someone that can match his energy.  

Thor is crazy sweet, has an awesome personality, and loves everyone. He is a bit timid when he first meets new dogs (who could blame him), but in a short time he gains his confidence and does well. Thor loves to go for walks. Thor is not only adorable, he's smart, sweet, and loves to be close. This boy is going to make some lucky person or family very happy with his unconditional love and devotion. Since Thor is still learning about life, we think he would do best as the only dog so he can have all of your attention. 

Want some more information?   Contact Jen at 602-820-5534 call or text E-mail:  Jen.PawsRescueAlliance@gmail.com

animal.description:
PAWS is currently closed due to COVID-19.  The animals are receiving the same high level of care as always.  During this time, we are taking application over the phone.  Until we can safely to resume normal operations, we will be taking deposits and doing adoptions by appointment only on Fridays and Saturdays from noon until 3.  We know it’s difficult to choose a lifetime companion animal from a picture but it’s been working out well for our adopters and most importantly, for the animals in our care. The financial impact is obvious but we're committed to keeping our community and volunteers as safe as possible and providing the best of care for our animals.  Any donations are greatly appreciated to help PAWS provided that care.  Thank you.

Oh what a handsome boy you are King.  King is only about 6 months old and weighs about 40 pounds right now.  He’ll be a nice sized guy when he’s all grown up.  His adoption fee is $200


All of our animals are provided with age appropriate vaccinations, spayed/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption. 
PAWS has added the H3N2/H3N8 combo flu vaccine to its shot protocol. Every dog is being vaccinated upon intake, however we urge adopters to get a second flu shot for their new family member to ensure as much protection against the flu as possible.
To meet our incredible dogs and offer them the love they deserve, stop by PAWS on Friday, Saturday or Sunday from 10 - 4 PM, call us at 217-243-7297. We do applications in person or over the phone. You can also see pictures on our Facebook page, PAWS Jackson.  With an approved application, a deposit will hold your new best friend for up to 1 week to allow you time to come to PAWS.  This deposit is not refundable nor transferable.

animal.description:
Meet Samson! This sweet and shy young dog came to us as a stray, and unfortunately he was skin and bones when he came in. Over the last couple weeks he has gained over 6 lbs, and while he still has some ways to go he appears to be a healthy and happy young pup. He can be slow to warm up to new people, but he loves neck scratches and playing with toys. He also is very interested in other dogs and has done well with another young dog we have at the shelter. 



Because he is a stray, there are still a lot of unknowns about how well he will adapt to a home environment. We're not sure he's potty-trained, and he startles easily at sudden movements or loud sounds. He will need a home that can provide a lot of training and guidance so he can grow into the best dog he can be. 



To inquire about Samson, send an application - http://www.seattle.gov/Documents/Departments/AnimalShelter/Dog%20Adoption%20Questionnaire_Fillable.pdf 

- to animalcare@seattle.gov
